title: DevOps/SRE Engineer, Security Gov Cloud
description:
The application window is expected to close on: February 28, 2025\\.  

*Job posting may be removed earlier if the position is filled or if a sufficient number of applications are received.*  

Please Note: The successful applicant will be performing work on US Government classified environments, and therefore, must be a U.S. Person (i.e., U.S. citizen, U.S. national, lawful permanent resident, asylee, or refugee). This position may also perform work that the U.S. government has specified can only be performed by a U.S. citizen on U.S. soil.  

  

Preference will be given to candidates located near Cisco hub offices in Austin TX, Raleigh NC and Fulton MD. **Who We Are**
Cisco Systems is offering an extraordinary opportunity to be part of a small, innovative team with a low process, high throughput culture. The team is working on Cisco Defense Orchestrator, Secure Firewall Migration Tool, cloud\\-delivered Cisco Secure Dynamic Attributes Connector and cloud\\-delivered Firewall Management Center which manages policy and configuration of Security Business Group's firewalls. We are looking for a DevOps Engineer to contribute to all parts of our infrastructure stack in both Government and Commercial clouds.  

**Who you’ll work with**
In this role, you will be part of a passionate multi\\-functional team that builds and improves our suite of offerings under Cisco Security Cloud. Our agile team is responsible for the design and deployment of end\\-to\\-end solutions/software for Firewall Policy use cases, Dynamic Objects using CSDAC and Firewall Configuration Migration use cases, implement CI/CD features and fix bugs as well as improving the DevOps processes in response to feedback. **What you’ll do**The DevOps Engineer is responsible for the production process, including continuous delivery of features, infrastructure automation, configuration management, high availability, and related tooling. You will interact with cross functional team members across Cisco (Architects, Product Owners, Product Managers) to review designs and arrive at suitable design and contribute to development and testing. You’ll ensure software is deployed and operated to the highest quality through reliable monitoring using observability tools.
Additional responsibilities include:
* Participate as a technical contributor on a fast\\-paced project team of engineers involved in the development of SaaS security products.
* Contribute to continously evolve cloud infrastructure, making it more resilient, scalable, and secure.
* Automate all manual procedures.
* Partner with the engineering organization to converge on common infrastructure setup, tooling, and deployment processes.
* Research and recommend technologies to help further product goals.
* Respond to and resolve infrastructure related critical issues.
* Manage and participate in on\\-call rotation, rotated through engineering team
* Collaborate with the greater Cisco technical support team

 **Minimum Qualifications*** BS/CS or related STEM degree with 7\\+ years of professional technical experience to include 5 years of DevOps related tasks in a SaaS environment that is hosted in AWS
* 5\\+ years of work within Linux based systems including use of Bash or related scripting languages (Example: General purpose language such as Ruby/Python).
* 3\\+ years of experience in the design, deployment, and operation of Kubernetes (AWS EKS) clusters and workloads.
* 4\\+ years of work with infrastructure automation tools such as Terraform, Ansible and CloudFormation
* 3\\+ years of setting up, configuring, maintaining, and evolving a CI/CD environment using tools such as Jenkins/Argo CD/TeamCity/Bamboo/etc.

 **Preferred Qualifications*** Create and manage a safe deployment procedure of new product changes across multiple environments (preferably backup/restore, secure credentials at rest like Vault);
* Ability to build SaaS monitoring solutions that detect and automatically remediate system faults (e.g. Datadog, Splunk)
* Triage, Debug and troubleshoot in a distributed environment.
* Understanding on computer system and network security.
* Agile software development.
* Collaboration skills, to reach out and triage critical issues in production that could be Priority 1, Priority 2

Partnering closely with developers, system and site reliability engineers, and customers, you'll analyze challenges and engineer robust solutions. Embracing cutting\\-edge CI/CD tools and containers, you'll automate deployment processes, optimizing efficiency. You'll implement solutions to bolster reliability by vigilantly monitoring application health and swiftly diagnosing issues. This is a highly technical, hands\\-on role that requires a wide and deep experience in leading infrastructure and applications. This role offers a tremendous amount of individual responsibility and influence over the direction of critical services for years to come. You are someone with ideas and a real passion for software delivered as a service to improve reuse, efficiency, and simplicity! Here you’ll find that we: • Have a peaceful work environment where you can choose when to socialize and when to focus. • Provide technical guidance and mentorship as needed • Have an encouraging and growth\\-focused workplace culture. • Encourage you to use accrued vacation time and maintain a healthy work\\-life balance. • Offer excellent benefits!

* Expertise in Go or Java programming and the ability to pivot to other languages as needed

* Leadership skills with the ability to mentor and inspire others.

**Preferred Qualifications**

A day in the life
The WWGST POS Tech (QA) Team engages in a variety of activities daily to ensure the quality, performance, and resilience of the Point of Sale (POS) system. The team focus on creating detailed test plans, developing both manual and automated test cases, and performing comprehensive functional, integration, and non\\-functional testing, including performance and scalability assessments. They also manage test environments, track and resolve defects, and conduct regression testing to maintain the integrity of existing features. By analyzing test results, providing insights, and continuously improving processes, the team ensures the POS system is production\\-ready and aligned with business goals.
About the team

title: Director, Marketing Analytics
description:
**About us**



At Auctane, we are united by a passion to help sellers — wherever they are, however they operate — fulfill the promises they make to consumers. The Auctane mission is to fuel commerce through exceptional delivery. We make it possible for businesses to meet the ever rising expectations of their customers, and we make the world smaller and more accessible to consumers everywhere. Auctane brands enable hundreds of thousands of merchants to annually deliver billions of products — over $200 billion worth — to customers around the globe. And Auctane is just getting started.



Auctane is a team of shipping and software experts with a passion for helping merchants move their ideas, dreams and innovations around the globe. The Auctane family includes ShipStation, Stamps.com, ShipEngine, Endicia, Metapack, GlobalPost, Packlink, and Return Rabbit. Our partners include Amazon, UPS, USPS, eBay, BigCommerce, Shopify, WooCommerce, and Walmart.


**Our values**



Win as One. Delight Customers. Deliver Great Outcomes.

**About the role**



As the Director, Marketing Analytics for all Auctane brands, you will play a pivotal role in transforming diverse marketing data streams into actionable, *prescriptive* insights that fuel strategic decision\\-making across our global marketing efforts. Your key responsibility will be to proactively guide the marketing organization in optimizing performance by identifying trends, opportunities, and challenges. More than just analyzing data, you will provide strategic recommendations to align marketing initiatives with overall business objectives, ensuring maximum efficiency and impact.



Leading a team of marketing analytics experts, you will foster a high\\-performing, data\\-driven culture, empowering your team to make informed decisions and deliver clear, actionable insights. Your leadership will drive the team's ability to forecast, optimize, and improve marketing strategies and tactics across all channels. Your mandate includes collaborating closely with cross\\-functional teams, ensuring analytics insights are seamlessly integrated into the broader marketing and data ecosystems.



The ideal candidate will combine deep expertise in marketing analytics with strategic vision and strong leadership capabilities. Your proven ability to deliver measurable business impact through data insights, coupled with your project management skills, will be critical in advancing Auctane's marketing efforts. You will wield data as a powerful strategic tool, propelling our brands forward in a competitive and fast\\-moving marketplace.



This position is **hybrid (3 days per week in office)** and is located in **Austin, Texas**


**What will you be doing?**



* **Optimize Marketing Performance Through Prescriptive, Data\\-Driven Insights and Advanced Analytics Techniques**


* Conduct proactive deep\\-dive analyses of marketing initiatives to understand performance drivers, uncover new growth opportunities, and apply advanced data science techniques to maximize impact.
* Move beyond descriptive analytics by incorporating prescriptive methods and marketing science principles to provide forward\\-looking recommendations for optimizing marketing strategies, including adjusting channel spend, website optimization, and experimentation.
* Build, enhance, and maintain sophisticated forecasting and driver\\-based models to predict future performance and support scenario planning, enabling marketing teams to simulate the impact of various strategies and tactics while making informed decisions based on robust data science methodologies.
* Translate complex insights into actionable recommendations by leveraging automated systems, dynamic algorithms, and advanced analytical approaches to optimize campaigns and strategies in real time as market conditions evolve.

* **Foster and Lead a High\\-Performance Advanced Marketing Analytics Team**


* Manage and mentor a team of Marketing Analysts dedicated to transforming marketing performance data into actionable insights, promoting a culture of continuous improvement, encouraging team members to stay updated on industry trends, advanced analytics techniques, and emerging automation tools.
* Guide the team's efforts to proactively identify optimization opportunities, combining traditional analysis with advanced analytics, statistical modeling, and code\\-based solutions to drive accuracy and efficiency in marketing performance evaluation.
* Facilitate collaboration across the team and departments, encouraging cross\\-functional projects that integrate advanced analytics and marketing science, fostering a blend of creativity and data\\-driven insights for innovative problem\\-solving.

title: Senior Software Development Lead with Data Focus
description:
Cisco ThousandEyes is a leading Digital Experience Assurance platform that empowers organizations to deliver flawless digital experiences across every network. Our platform is powered by AI and an unmatched set of cloud, internet, and enterprise network telemetry data. As a member of our Alerts team, you'll focus on building a highly scalable stream processing platform to detect anomalies and provide actionable insights to our customers.

We use technologies such as Flink, Kafka, Debezium, and Elasticache to execute multiple complex rules and statistical models to detect anomalies across billions of events. You'll contribute to our real-time data platform, build microservices that power critical business workflows, ensure systems are operational, and adhere to strict SLAs. The Alerts platform is critical for our customers to act on potential problems in their mission-critical systems.

If you're passionate about working with huge amounts of data and turning them into powerful insights to improve the quality of the internet, this is your team. As a Senior software engineer on our team, you'll have the opportunity to dive into the exciting realm of machine learning, develop cutting-edge anomaly detection algorithms, and construct high-performance micro-services contributing to the speed and accuracy of alert events.

We're looking for someone with strong computer science fundamentals, object-oriented design skills, and proven leadership in guiding software development teams. If you have a background in building large-scale data processing systems and working in a fast-paced development environment, this role might be perfect for you.

title: Data & Analytics Lead Engineer - Advanced Analytics
description:

Specific responsibilities include but are not limited to:
• Perform duties related to business analysis, such as scoping, documentation, project management, and related activities to establish an engagement blueprint

• Rapidly develop diverse POCs from various data sources and systems

• Balance multiple projects with attention to detail while meeting deadlines
• Continuously improve processes with advancements in the MS BI platform

Qualifications
• Master's or Bachelor's degree in a relevant field (such as Computer Science, Information Systems, Data Science, or a related discipline).
• 8+ years of experience in a data analyst, developer, architect, or similar position
• 7+ years of advanced experience with DAX, M, SQL, and Power BI

• 1.5+ years of experience in leveraging ETL SaaS tools (Talent, Stitch, Hevo, etc.,) or ADF Integration

• Expert skills in Microsoft Excel and Outlook, strong skills in PowerPoint

• Excellent client-facing and internal communication skills
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills
• Effectively managing multiple deliverables, clients, and projects in a fast-paced environment
• Knowledge of programming languages like SQL, Python, R, or Java.
• Familiarity with data governance, data security, and compliance.
• Strong problem-solving skills and analytical thinking.

Key Stakeholders This Role Interacts With:

Internal
• Senior BI Analyst
• Data Product Manager
• BI Architect / Senior Architect
• Data Engineers
• Analytics Developers (Power BI, Tableau)

External
• C-Suite Executives (CEO, CFO, CIO, etc.)
• Clients Operations Leads and Mid-Level Managers
• Data Owners, Data Stewards
• Enterprise Information Management and Data Governance Team
• IT Staff – Architects, DBAs, Developers, etc.

We expect the candidate to uphold Crowe’s values of Care, Trust, Courage, and Stewardship. These values define who we are. We expect all of our people to act ethically and with integrity at all times.

The application deadline for this role is 04/04/2025.

The wage range for this role takes into account the wide range of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions including but not limited to skill sets; experience and training; licensure and certifications; and other business and organizational needs. The disclosed range estimate has not been adjusted for the applicable geographic differential associated with the location at which the position may be filled. At Crowe, it is not typical for an individual to be hired at or near the top of the range for their role and compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. A reasonable estimate of the current range is $104,500.00 - $208,300.00 per year.

Our Benefits:

Your exceptional people experience starts here. At Crowe, we know that great people are what makes a great firm. We care about our people and offer employees a comprehensive total rewards package. Learn more about what working at Crowe can mean for you!

How You Can Grow:

We will nurture your talent in an inclusive culture that values diversity. You will have the chance to meet on a consistent basis with your Career Coach that will guide you in your career goals and aspirations. Learn more about where talent can prosper!

More about Crowe:

Crowe (www.crowe.com) is one of the largest public accounting, consulting and technology firms in the United States. Crowe uses its deep industry expertise to provide audit services to public and private entities while also helping clients reach their goals with tax, advisory, risk and performance services. Crowe is recognized by many organizations as one of the country's best places to work. Crowe serves clients worldwide as an independent member of Crowe Global, one of the largest global accounting networks in the world. The network consists of more than 200 independent accounting and advisory services firms in more than 130 countries around the world.

Crowe LLP provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws.

Any referrals, resumes or candidates submitted to Crowe, or any employee or owner of Crowe without a pre-existing agreement signed by both parties covering the submission will be considered the property of Crowe, and free of charge.

Crowe will consider for employment all qualified applicants, including those with criminal histories, in a manner consistent with the requirements of applicable state and local laws. Please visit our webpage to see notices of the various state and local Ban-the-Box laws and Fair Chance Ordinances, where applicable.

title: Software Engineering Intermediate Software Developer
description:
Company Overview:  



**Work Where it Matters**

  

Systems Intelligence, an Akima company, is not just another federal IT contractor. As an Alaska Native Corporation (ANC), our mission and purpose extend beyond our exciting federal projects as we support our shareholder communities in Alaska.

  

At Systems Intelligence, the work you do every day makes a difference in the lives of our 15,000 Iñupiat shareholders, a group of Alaska natives from one of the most remote and harshest environments in the United States.

 **For our shareholders,** Systems Intelligence provides support and employment opportunities and contributes to the survival of a culture that has thrived above the Arctic Circle for more than 10,000 years.

 **For our government customers,** Systems Intelligence delivers innovative information technology solutions that evolve and modernize IT infrastructures.

 **As a Systems Intelligence employee,** you will be surrounded by a challenging, yet supportive work environment that is committed to innovation and diversity, two of our most important values. You will also have access to our comprehensive benefits and competitive pay in addition to growth opportunities and excellent retirement options.


Description:

Systems Intelligence is excited to uphold the Army Software Factory’s mission of enabling Soldiers to become software professionals. We are looking for a Software Engineering Intermediate Software Developer to ensure and enforce ASWF practices are followed within their assigned Software Development Unit.

  

Travel:

  

Anticipated travel is approximately 4 \\- 8 trips per contract year with each trip lasting a full work week, however, further travel is at the discretion of the government based on mission needs.

  

Shift:

  

Core business hours of 8:45 A.M through 5:15 P.M central time, Monday through Friday, with eight working (non\\-lunch) hours per day


Prescribed period during which lunch may be taken: 11:00 A.M. and 1:00 P.M.


Responsibilities:

As a senior practitioner in their craft, the individual who fills this role is responsible mentoring and guiding Coaches for continuous, integrated alignment in support of ASWF enablement. Responsibilities include:

* Executing practice standards.
* Addressing acute needs within the SDU.
* Radiating insights for practice health, check\\-ins, and assessments across SDUs and within the Learning Office to whom they are accountable to.
* Leverage tools and processes to enable the SDUs to adapt to emerging needs.
* Supporting novice Soldiers when dedicated pairs are unavailable.
* Providing rapid practice feedback to practitioners.


Qualifications:
* 5 years of experience as a Software Engineer.
* 2 years’ experience coaching and coordinating work done of teams with functions (like software engineers, security, compliance, data scientists, and product designers).
* Ability to coach and train intermediate software developers in training and junior software developers in the following:
* + Execute software planning, requirements, risk management, design, development, architecture, modeling, estimation, configuration management, quality, security, and tests using software development methodologies, architectural structures, viewpoints, styles, design decisions, and frameworks across all lifecycle phases.
* Fluent in test driven development, lean methodology, and DevSecOps.
* Knowledge of Java, C\\#, Spring Boot, PHP, Typescript/JavaScript, NodeJs, Python, Kotlin, and programming language or data structures and logic to transform and visualize data as needed.
* Ability to obtain interim Secret clearance prior to start date and achieve/maintain Secret clearance upon final adjudication.


Benefits Description: Regular \\- The company offers a comprehensive benefits program, including medical, dental, vision, life insurance, 401(k) and a range of other voluntary benefits. Paid Time Off (PTO) is offered to regular full\\-time and eligible part\\-time employees. Job ID: 2025\\-15801 Work Type: Remote

Description:

Systems Intelligence is excited to uphold the Army Software Factory’s mission of enabling Soldiers to become software professionals. We are looking for a Software Engineering Practice Lead to enable others in a one\\-to\\-many model, focusing their efforts on activities that scale to many practitioners at once and cultivating an environment for continuous practice improvement. The Practice Lead establishes core practices, drives continuous learning, deliberately coaches for professional growth, curates learning resources and coordinates with Executive Leadership in standardizing enablement practices for the organization.

  

Travel:

  

CONUS travel in performance of the contract will be determined at the time of need.

  

Shift:

  

Core business hours of 8:45 A.M through 5:15 P.M central time, Monday through Friday, with eight working (non\\-lunch) hours per day

Responsibilities:

The Practice Lead is the principal assessor for all personnel in the unit with corresponding practice and is responsible for performing the following duties:

* Executes lean and agile rituals and methodology.
* Develops and implements customer practices.
* Measures the health of practice.
* Responsible for professional growth and development of 6\\-8 Soldiers.
* Coaches and mentors to progress Soldier competencies.
* Serve as senior expert in their technical craft who translates that expertise to coach and enable at appropriate audience level to include novice, junior, intermediate, senior, and/or executive.
* Support the Learning and Product Office to inform and evolve the skills matrix, adapting and adding skills to the changing needs of the customer, which may require developing the skills matrix for a new language, new software frameworks, or similar, and recommendations and curriculum to train end users on the new skills.
* Contribute training support and planning to practice times and training events.
* Draft agendas and training plans.
* Transfer knowledge via tangible program documentation and support to training events, both recurring and ad hoc (e.g., Hackathon).
* Support evaluation and recommendation regarding technologies that can and should be used to enable ASWF practices.


Qualifications:
* 10 years of experience as Software Engineer.
* 3 years in the DoD.
* 5 years’ experience in coaching and training senior developers and intermediate developers in the following: software planning, requirements, risk management, design, development, architecture, modeling, estimation, configuration management, quality, security, and tests using software development methodologies, architectural structures, viewpoints, styles, design decisions, and frameworks across all lifecycle phases.
* Fluent in test driven development, lean methodology, and DevSecOps.
* Knowledge of Java, C\\#, Spring Boot, PHP, Typescript/JavaScript, NodeJs, Python, Kotlin, and programming language or data structures and logic to transform and visualize data as needed.
* Ability to obtain interim Secret clearance prior to start date and achieve/maintain Secret clearance upon final adjudication.

title: Software Development Engineer - Triton Kernels
description:
Overview:
**WHAT YOU DO AT AMD CHANGES EVERYTHING**

We care deeply about transforming lives with AMD technology to enrich our industry, our communities, and the world. Our mission is to build great products that accelerate next\\-generation computing experiences – the building blocks for the data center, artificial intelligence, PCs, gaming and embedded. Underpinning our mission is the AMD culture. We push the limits of innovation to solve the world’s most important challenges. We strive for execution excellence while being direct, humble, collaborative, and inclusive of diverse perspectives.

AMD together we advance\\_
Responsibilities:
**SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT ENG****INEER**  

  

**THE ROLE:**  

AMD is looking for an AI software development engineer to develop ML kernels in the Triton kernel language. We are looking for an engineer who is passionate about optimizing Machine Learning GPU kernels and improving the performance of key applications and benchmarks**.** What you do directly impacts the performance of AMD GPUs and enables us to become a competitive solution for generative AI. Become a part of our high\\-impact and incredibly talented Triton kernels team. **THE PERSON:**
The ideal candidate should have experience in parallel computer architecture and high performance GPU kernel development. Additional experience developing ML models and knowledge of ML frameworks like PyTorch or JAX is a plus. **KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:*** Develop ML kernels for matrix multiplication, Flash Attention and other ML operators
* Benchmark, perform competitive analysis and optimize your kernels to improve performance
* Propose novel optimizations to the Triton compiler
* Collaborate with the GPU architecture team to improve future generations
* Apply knowledge of software engineering best practices

 **PREFERRED EXPERIENCE:*** Programming experience on GPUs \\- HIP, CUDA, OpenCL or Triton
* ML experience or knowledge in one or more of the following areas \\- Transformers, image models, recommendation systems
* Ability to work independently, define project goals and scope, and lead your own development effort
* Experience using debuggers
* Familiarity with PyTorch or JAX
* Knowledge of MLIR, LLVM and GPU assembly and GPU architecture is a plus
* Familiarity with models like LLama, Mixtral and Gemma is a plus

 **ACADEMIC CREDENTIALS:*** Master's degree or PhD in Computer Science or Computer Engineering or equivalent


\\#LI\\-JG1


Qualifications:

At AMD, your base pay is one part of your total rewards package. Your base pay will depend on where your skills, qualifications, experience, and location fit into the hiring range for the position. You may be eligible for incentives based upon your role such as either an annual bonus or sales incentive. Many AMD employees have the opportunity to own shares of AMD stock, as well as a discount when purchasing AMD stock if voluntarily participating in AMD’s Employee Stock Purchase Plan. You’ll also be eligible for competitive benefits described in more detail here. *AMD does not accept unsolicited resumes from headhunters, recruitment agencies, or fee\\-based recruitment services. AMD and its subsidiaries are equal opportunity, inclusive employers and will consider all applicants without regard to age, ancestry, color, marital status, medical condition, mental or physical disability, national origin, race, religion, political and/or third\\-party affiliation, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. We encourage applications from all qualified candidates and will accommodate applicants’ needs under the respective laws throughout all stages of the recruitment and selection process.*

title: Senior Rust API Engineer
description:
About Us.
DroneSense offers a drone software platform tailored for the unique needs of the public safety market. Our comprehensive solution equips First Responders with a complete tool set that expands situational awareness and acts as a force multiplier. Our mission\\-critical platform solves the challenges of scale and operational deployment across an entire organization, ultimately leading to more saved lives. Drones are a game\\-changer for the way First Responders carry out their various missions. DroneSense is here to serve as an integral part of this evolution in public safety.  

Our Culture.
We are a founder\\-led company and our leadership team is made of experienced engineers, pilots, and entrepreneurs. Our core values are central to how we work together as a team, solve problems for our customers and make decisions. We are looking for people who see problems as opportunities, have a growth mindset, and are willing to challenge the status quo. Our team is focused on helping our customers by making their jobs easier through technology. We do this through creative problem solving and rolling up our sleeves to get the job done together. We are trying to build a diverse team and value what each individual brings to the team. We want our team members to have fun, be themselves and feel a sense of belonging at DroneSense.
### **Primary Responsibilities**

* Create and enhance RESTful, WebSocket, and MQTT based APIs using Rust
* Migrate existing APIs from C\\# to Rust
* Use Rust to integrate with 3rd party cloud services
* Follow and evolve Rust development best practices
* Fly drones to test and validate your API changes and integrations

### **Requirements**

* Must have 4\\+ years experience with Rust
* At least 5\\+ years building customer/partner facing APIs
* Experience with some or all of the following: Async Rust, Tokio, Axum, Tungstenite, and WebSockets
* Experience with mTLS, API Keys, or other connection authentication approaches
* Ability to work well within a team but on individual projects
* Excited to work with drones, robotics and first responders

### **Our Technology**

* Rust
* WebSockets
* MySQL
* MQTT
* SignalR
* Protobuf
* GitLab CI
* **DroneSense employees full time US citizens who are current residence in one of the 50 contiguous United States. Though our positions are "remote" we do not work with offshore/near shore individuals or contractors to stay in compliance with our client's requirements.**

 **Benefits*** Competitive Base Pay
* Stock Options
* Medical, Dental, and Vision, including a medical plan with 100% employee covered premium
* Company paid Life Insurance, Short \\& Long Term Disability
* Medical FSA \\& Dependent Care Account
* 401(k)
* Work from Home
* Paid Flexible Time Off
* Paid Sick Time
* Part 107 Pilot Training \\& License Paid

title: Senior Software Engineer (DevOps)
description:
SkyGrid, a Boeing, Avathon Company, exists to open the sky for autonomous flight. Based in Austin, Texas, SkyGrid builds ground based high\\-assurance third\\-party services to enable the safe operations and airspace integration of highly automated and autonomous aircraft. SkyGrid also acts as a key operational nexus for advanced air mobility, integrating and managing data, infrastructure, access, and traffic to support seamless and efficient air traffic services.  

SkyGrid is seeking a talented Senior Software Engineer with DevOps experience to support our Autonomy R\\&D team. This role focuses on the rapid integration and deployment of algorithms, developed by R\\&D and Autonomy engineers, into cloud\\-based lab environments and simulations. This person will play a key role in end\\-to\\-end testing of next\\-generation autonomous air traffic management functions for Advanced Air Mobility (AAM), from concept to prototype.  

SkyGrid is committed to promoting an inclusive and lively culture that paves the way for opportunities and growth while remaining flexible in an ever\\-changing environment.
### **Performance Objectives:**

* Streamline deployment of prototypical functions in various internal and external lab/sim environments.
* Implementation of a robust CI/CD pipeline ensuring high code quality, reuse, and security via automation.
* Implementation of an automated system for running and tracking all lab/sim data.
* Support upcoming SIL/HIL simulation activities.
* Successfully support multiple prototypical functions in internal and external simulation labs.
* Advance the R\\&D infrastructure and automation capabilities to support data analysis and algorithmic improvement.

### **Responsibilities:**

* Closely work with Autonomy R\\&D engineers to develop software wrappers, APIs, databases and automation frameworks for integrating functional prototypes into lab environments and simulations.
* Manage cloud infrastructure (AWS, Kubernetes, Docker), optimize CI/CD pipelines, and implement Infrastructure\\-as\\-Code (Terraform/CloudFormation).
* Manage and secure AWS cloud infrastructure, including VPCs, VPNs, and firewalls.
* Support SIL (Software\\-in\\-the\\-Loop) and HIL (Hardware\\-in\\-the\\-Loop) simulations for validating aerospace autonomy functions.
* Work in an Agile/Scrum environment, document workflows, and handle controlled information (CUI, export\\-controlled).

### **Qualifications:**

* B.S. in Computer Science or a related field
* Work experience in software development
* Programming Languages: Python, JavaScript, MATLAB, C/C\\+\\+ and Simulink
* Infrastructure as Code (Pulumi, Terraform)
* Cloud Deployment (AWS/GCP/Azure, Kubernetes)
* DevOps Support (CI/CD pipelines, automated testing, deployment, and version control systems)
* Software\\-in\\-the\\-Loop (SIL) and Hardware\\-in\\-the\\-Loop (HIL) simulation development

### **Preferred Qualifications:**

* 5\\-10 years of software engineering experience, with a strong focus on DevOps and cloud infrastructure.
* Experience deploying resources in AWS (or a similar cloud provider).
* Experience with automation, CI/CD, and infrastructure as code tools like Pulumi, Terraform, or CloudFormation.
* Strong proficiency in distributed systems, networking protocols, API design, and SQL database management.
* Experience with messaging systems such as RabbitMQ, SQS, or Kafka for event\\-driven architectures
* Experience with simulation technologies · Familiarity with AI/ML, robotics, or autonomous systems.
* Master's degree in computer science or related field, or equivalent industry experience.
* Key Cloud Certifications: AWS Certified DevOps Engineer, AWS Certified SysOps Administrator, AWS Certified Solutions Architect, AWS Certified Security – Specialty, Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA), Certified Cloud Security Professional (CCSP).
* Key Cybersecurity Certifications: CompTIA Security\\+, CISSP, CCNA.

### **Join Our Team and Enjoy Exceptional Benefits:**

* **Comprehensive Health Coverage from Day One**: Enjoy immediate access to medical, dental, and vision insurance, including HSA and FSA options.
* **Generous Retirement Contributions**: Benefit from an automatic company 401k contribution program, with no match required, plus an additional company matching program to boost your retirement savings.
* **Calm Annual Membership**: Prioritize your mental health with complimentary access to mindfulness and meditation resources.
* **Discounted ClassPass Membership**: Stay active and healthy with access to thousands of fitness studios and gyms nationwide.
* **Investment in Your Growth**: Receive an annual stipend for learning and development to support your continuous education and skill development
* **Engaging Team Activities**: Participate in quarterly team\\-building events and celebrations organized by our dedicated culture committee.
* **Fully Stocked Kitchen**: Enjoy a variety of snacks and beverages to keep you fueled throughout the day.

title: Sr. Principal Firmware Engineer
description:
If you are looking for a challenging and exciting career in the world of technology, then look no further. Skyworks is an innovator of high\\-performance analog semiconductors whose solutions are powering the wireless networking revolution. Through our broad technology expertise and one of the most extensive product portfolios in the industry, we are **Connecting Everyone and Everything, All the Time**.

  

At Skyworks, you will find a fast\\-paced environment with a strong focus on global collaboration, minimal layers of management, and the freedom to make meaningful contributions in a setting that encourages creative thinking. We value open communication, mutual trust, and respect. We are excited about the opportunity to work with you and glad you want to be part of a team of talented individuals who together are changing the way the world communicates.


Requisition ID: 74196

**Job Description**
-------------------

**The Role**


We are looking for a proactive, detail\\-oriented, hands\\-on, results\\-driven Senior Principal Firmware Engineer who is passionate about making our customers successful, welcomes challenges with enthusiasm and thrives in a dynamic and fast\\-paced environment, to become an integral part of our Broadcast team. The Senior Principal Firmware Engineer will play key roles in system architecture, embedded firmware implementation, and technical leadership.

 **Responsibilities**

* Work closely with firmware, applications, hardware, marketing, and customer teams on multiple projects to:
* Understand, partition and document features, specifications, and dependencies
* Define and develop flexible and scalable firmware architectures and internal and external APIs
* Design and develop broadcast radio firmware elements, including features, infrastructure components, and interfaces
* Work with teams on system integration, resource management, performance evaluation, testing, debugging, deployment, and customer support
* Peer Code reviewing
**Qualifications**
------------------

* MS in EE/ECE and 12\\+ years of hands\\-on embedded firmware MCU development OR
* BS in EE/ECE and 15\\+ years
* PhD in EE/ECE and 8\\+ years


Background in one or more of the following areas is required

* Strong embedded firmware development in C/C\\+\\+
* Embedded firmware architecture and product specification, development, and validation
* RTOS development/integration in a multi\\-core environment
* Continuous Integration (CI) Development and Deployment
* Scripting languages, e.g., Python, TCL or similar

description:
#### **About us**



Coalition is the world's first Active Insurance provider designed to help prevent digital risk before it strikes. Founded in 2017, Coalition combines broad insurance coverage with a digital risk assessment and continuous security monitoring to help organizations protect themselves in today's hyper\\-connected world.



Opportunities to make an impact with bold thinking are real \\- and happening daily.

#### **About the role**



Coalition is looking for an experienced insurance data modeler to help build out our world\\-class modeling team. You will be responsible to create and maintain data and modeling pipelines for many key pricing functions across the cyber and executive risk lines. This role comes with a significant focus on the optimization of our processes in order to improve our efficiencies, enhance our monitoring framework and ease our ability to take data\\-driven decisions. You will work in a collaborative cross\\-functional environment to develop new ways to understand cyber risk in order to optimize our rating structure.



We're looking for someone who will roll up their sleeves and push boundaries, innovate and explore new techniques and improvements to enhance our value propos



#### **Responsibilities**


* Core price modeling responsibilities include:
	+ Development and maintenance of actuarial data pipelines with relevant metrics and analysis that are scalable, efficient, accurate and complete, to enable data\\-informed pricing decisions
	+ Automation and enhancement of actuarial processes in reserving, pricing and actuarial modeling teams
	+ Development of risk controls, including price monitoring and early warning indicators
	+ Development of tools to assess model \\& business performance, including UI dashboards
	+ Seek innovative opportunities to enhance model performance through new data, features or modeling techniques
	+ Perform, document and present ad hoc quantitative analysis
* Straddle the worlds of insurance, data science, engineering and security experts to shape the most suitable data\\-driven solutions
* Act as an ambassador to get model users buy\\-in through strong collaboration with all relevant partners

#### **Skills and Qualifications**


* 3\\+ years of experience in insurance predictive modeling
* Undergraduate degree in Actuarial Science, Data Science or any other related field
* Strong programming skills in Python, SQL and/or R
* Ability to build transactional data pipelines
* Excellent communication skills including ability to simplify complex technical concepts to non\\-technical audiences
* Ability to take ambiguous problems and solve them in a structured data\\-driven way
* Intellectual curiosity and an interest in our mission of solving cyber risk
* Strong understanding of actuarial pricing concepts
* Ability to work efficiently in a fast paced environment, be creative and think outside the box

#### **Bonus Points**


* Cyber and/or executive liability experience
* Has completed some actuarial exams
* Master degree in Data Science or Actuarial Science
* Ability to build UI/UX design

#### **Compensation**



Our compensation reflects the cost of labor across several US geographic markets. The US base salary for this position ranges from $121,000year in our lowest geographic market up to $156,000/year in our highest geographic market. #### **Why Coalition?**



We're a remote\\-first, mission\\-driven team committed to building a more inclusive culture with people of all different backgrounds. We trust our team members to take responsibility, share ownership, and put in the work to help us in our pursuit to solve digital risk.



Coalition's exceptional growth stems from its ability to address real\\-world problems for organizations of all sizes and remain true to our founding values of character, humility, responsibility, purpose, authenticity, and inclusion.

title: Director, Marketing Analytics
description:
**About us**



At Auctane, we are united by a passion to help sellers — wherever they are, however they operate — fulfill the promises they make to consumers. The Auctane mission is to fuel commerce through exceptional delivery. We make it possible for businesses to meet the ever rising expectations of their customers, and we make the world smaller and more accessible to consumers everywhere. Auctane brands enable hundreds of thousands of merchants to annually deliver billions of products — over $200 billion worth — to customers around the globe. And Auctane is just getting started.



Auctane is a team of shipping and software experts with a passion for helping merchants move their ideas, dreams and innovations around the globe. The Auctane family includes ShipStation, Stamps.com, ShipEngine, Endicia, Metapack, GlobalPost, Packlink, and Return Rabbit. Our partners include Amazon, UPS, USPS, eBay, BigCommerce, Shopify, WooCommerce, and Walmart.


**Our values**



Win as One. Delight Customers. Deliver Great Outcomes.

**About the role**



As the Director, Marketing Analytics for all Auctane brands, you will play a pivotal role in transforming diverse marketing data streams into actionable, *prescriptive* insights that fuel strategic decision\\-making across our global marketing efforts. Your key responsibility will be to proactively guide the marketing organization in optimizing performance by identifying trends, opportunities, and challenges. More than just analyzing data, you will provide strategic recommendations to align marketing initiatives with overall business objectives, ensuring maximum efficiency and impact.



Leading a team of marketing analytics experts, you will foster a high\\-performing, data\\-driven culture, empowering your team to make informed decisions and deliver clear, actionable insights. Your leadership will drive the team's ability to forecast, optimize, and improve marketing strategies and tactics across all channels. Your mandate includes collaborating closely with cross\\-functional teams, ensuring analytics insights are seamlessly integrated into the broader marketing and data ecosystems.



The ideal candidate will combine deep expertise in marketing analytics with strategic vision and strong leadership capabilities. Your proven ability to deliver measurable business impact through data insights, coupled with your project management skills, will be critical in advancing Auctane's marketing efforts. You will wield data as a powerful strategic tool, propelling our brands forward in a competitive and fast\\-moving marketplace.



This position is **hybrid (3 days per week in office)** and is located in **Austin, Texas**


**What will you be doing?**



* **Optimize Marketing Performance Through Prescriptive, Data\\-Driven Insights and Advanced Analytics Techniques**


* Conduct proactive deep\\-dive analyses of marketing initiatives to understand performance drivers, uncover new growth opportunities, and apply advanced data science techniques to maximize impact.
* Move beyond descriptive analytics by incorporating prescriptive methods and marketing science principles to provide forward\\-looking recommendations for optimizing marketing strategies, including adjusting channel spend, website optimization, and experimentation.
* Build, enhance, and maintain sophisticated forecasting and driver\\-based models to predict future performance and support scenario planning, enabling marketing teams to simulate the impact of various strategies and tactics while making informed decisions based on robust data science methodologies.
* Translate complex insights into actionable recommendations by leveraging automated systems, dynamic algorithms, and advanced analytical approaches to optimize campaigns and strategies in real time as market conditions evolve.

* **Foster and Lead a High\\-Performance Advanced Marketing Analytics Team**


* Manage and mentor a team of Marketing Analysts dedicated to transforming marketing performance data into actionable insights, promoting a culture of continuous improvement, encouraging team members to stay updated on industry trends, advanced analytics techniques, and emerging automation tools.
* Guide the team's efforts to proactively identify optimization opportunities, combining traditional analysis with advanced analytics, statistical modeling, and code\\-based solutions to drive accuracy and efficiency in marketing performance evaluation.
* Facilitate collaboration across the team and departments, encouraging cross\\-functional projects that integrate advanced analytics and marketing science, fostering a blend of creativity and data\\-driven insights for innovative problem\\-solving.

* **Enhance Reporting Processes with Automation and Code\\-Based Solutions**


* Direct the development of automated, code\\-driven measurement frameworks that align with Auctane's business and marketing objectives, freeing up time for deeper analysis while ensuring consistent, accurate, and timely delivery of key metrics (in accordance with data definitions accepted across the business).
* Design user\\-friendly reporting systems that distill complex data and marketing science insights into *actionable* insights, enabling technical and non\\-technical stakeholders to easily understand and act on the data.
* Oversee the creation and maintenance of dashboards and reports that provide ongoing visibility into key marketing metrics, leveraging automation to reduce manual intervention.
* Continuously optimize reporting processes, using code to automate recurring reports, streamline ad\\-hoc analysis, and ensure the timely delivery of accurate data insights.
* Use historical data (internal and external) and trends to forecast future performance, offering prescriptive insights on the optimal deployment of upcoming marketing initiatives.

* **Drive Cross\\-Functional Data Alignment Across GTM functions**


* Regularly present actionable insights to stakeholders, including senior leadership, using clear, concise reports, dashboards, and presentations that highlight key trends and recommendations.
* Collaborate with marketing operations, data definitions committee, and internal/external partners to monitor and resolve data quality issues, ensuring data consistency and reliability in order to maintain consistency across all marketing data streams and platforms.
* Promote a Data\\-Driven Culture by continuously advocating for data\\-driven decision\\-making across the organization, demonstrating the value of analytics in informing strategic and tactical decisions, and building trust in data as a key asset.
* Leverage automated tools to continuously monitor data integrity, troubleshoot discrepancies, and ensure seamless integration of data across the organization.


**What are we looking for?**


* Masters Degree in Marketing, Economics, Statistics, or any quantitative discipline preferred.
* Minimum of 10\\+ years of experience in marketing analytics, with a proven track record of delivering insights and recommendations that drove measurable business impact
* Minimum of 5\\-7 years of directly managing analytics professionals
* Strong analytical skills and experience working with large and complex datasets, including advanced proficiency in Excel/Google Sheets and SQL
* Expert knowledge of web analytics tools such as Google Analytics, Adobe Analytics, or similar
* Proven track record of working within marketing automation platforms and tools such as Marketo, HubSpot, Eloqua, or similar, as well as Salesforce and Salesforce reporting tools
* In\\-depth familiarity with BI and data visualization tools such as Tableau, Looker, or similar.
* Excellent communication skills, with the ability to distill complex data and insights into clear and concise reports and presentations
* Statistical programming experience in R, Python, RStudio
* Expertise in statistical analysis around A/B/multivariate testing, incrementality tests
* Familiarity with multitouch and marketing mix models
* Ability to work in a dynamic, fast paced environment and deliver to deadlines
* Ability to question the staquo, test\\-and\\-learn and look for continuous improvement opportunities


**The Tech**


* SQL
* R/Python
* BigQuery/Redshift
* Excel/Google Sheets
* Posit Connect
* Looker/Tableau
* Hubspot/Marketo/Salesforce
* G\\-suite


**What do we offer?**


* We are a hybrid company. All team members at Auctane in Austin come into the office Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays.
* Take the reins of your time off with our Flex Time Off policy – because work\\-life balance should always be in your hands!
* We offer 12 paid holidays for all of our US employees!
* 401k employer matching program – because your future deserves a friendly boost!
* + ️We conduct annual merit reviews to recognize and reward your hard work and achievements.
* ️ Company events, we work hard, play hard! We do our best every day, even at our regular team\\-building events.
* Attractive office space in the heart of central Austin, Texas (free drinks, snacks…).
* Indulge in weekly catered lunches at our office – a delicious perk to fuel your work.
* Health and Wellness: The well\\-being of our team is super important to us. Choose from different options that include medical, dental, and vision plans.
* + ️Fitness center in the office with Tonal Mirrors, Pelotons, free weights, etc.
* Employee Assistance Program. We offer up to 8 free mental health sessions.
* We offer gym discounts to help you stay fit and healthy!
* We offer education reimbursement to all employees, ensuring that you can pursue your educational goals while excelling in your career with us. Invest in your future and let us support your growth every step of the way.
* Employee Referral Program! We reward employees helping us find top talent!
* An inclusive, casual and upbeat work environment. The personality and opinions of each of our team members are important and valid; we aim to offer all employees a safe environment where they can be themselves and thrive.


**Additional Position Duties:** (The following is a list of what all employees, except those with medical accommodation, may be regularly required to do.)


* Sit for prolonged periods of time
* Utilize wrist and hands for a prolonged period of time
* Walk short distances
* Stand for short periods
* Speaking and conversing with others
* Lift up to 25lbs without assistance up to chest height


**Equal Opportunity Employer/Veterans/Disabled**



If you are based in California, we encourage you to read this important information about the ShipStation Privacy Policy for California residents linked here.

title: Java Developer
description:
**Your opportunity**
--------------------

  

At Schwab, you’re empowered to make an impact on your career. Here, innovative thought meets creative problem solving, helping us “challenge the status quo” and transform the finance industry together.  

The Client Experiences and Preferences (CEP) Technology organization at Schwab is comprised of teams that support Schwab business goals through the delivery of technology solutions that focus on providing enhancements and functionalities that are needed to support our client's offers, preferences, and eligibility information. CEP Technology is looking for a motivated and energetic, experienced senior developer to advance our platform offerings.  

The role will work with technical and business partners to design and maintain optimal programming and environment solutions. Job activities will involve researching and documenting production environments, architecture, developing solutions and supporting the tools and processes to gather detailed user requirements, architecting/developing a solution, and driving strategic planning discussions with technical, business, and client stakeholders. **What you’ll do:*** Work with technical and business experts to create and support optimal production and test environment solutions

**What you have**

 **Required Qualifications:*** 4\\-6 years of experience with the following: Java, Spring framework, cloud development, and Web Services (REST) supporting high volume transactions in a Highly Available environment
* 1\\-2 years of experience using Python.
* 2\\+ years' of experience in Cloud deployment in a continuous integration and continuous delivery model (CI/CD)

* Experience with the Atlassian tool stack (JIRA et alia)
* Experience with .NET framework and programming tools (Visual Studio) and C\\# is a plus
* Experience in RabbitMQ is a plus
* Experience in Financial Services industry is a plus
* Experience in Test Driven Development is a plus

 **Preferred Qualifications:*** Outstanding verbal and written communication skills
* Ability to analyze and solve problems creatively
* Ability to meet deadlines, goals and objectives
* Ability to work collaboratively with internal and external stakeholders including offshore teams and manage offshore development activities

------------------------


At Schwab, we’re committed to empowering our employees’ personal and professional success. title: Graduate Product Analyst
description:
**Company Description**  

Wise is a global technology company, building the best way to move and manage the world’s money.  

**Min fees. Max ease. Full speed.**


Whether people and businesses are sending money to another country, spending abroad, or making and receiving international payments, Wise is on a mission to make their lives easier and save them money.


As part of our team, you will be helping us create an entirely new network for the world's money.  

**For everyone, everywhere.**


More about **our mission** and **what we offer**.

 **Job Description**  

As a Graduate Product Analyst, you’ll join our Analytics team in September 2025\\. This full\\-time role offers a chance to make a meaningful impact and kickstart your career. You’ll be onboarded with the global Graduate cohort in one of our offices and learn the basics of being a Wiser.

**You'll be a part of the Regional North America Analytics squad where you will:**

* Be a strategy partner to Regional North America product managers and engineers to help shape the future of the North America Wise product
* Collaborate with cross\\-functional teams, including product managers, engineers, bankers, as well as global analytics teams, to foster innovative solutions and gain a comprehensive understanding of the product.
* Assist in building and optimizing data infrastructure and pipelines using tools like dBt, Snowflake, Looker, and Superset that support strategic, data\\-driven decisions for the team.

**You’ll be a part of one of the following teams:**

* **NorthAm Verification team** that focuses on understanding and enhancing KYC/KYB (Know Your Customer / Know Your Business) experience for customers. Here you will identify and address customer pain points in the verification funnel, contributing strategies to streamline the onboarding process and enhance user experience.
* **NorthAm Wise Account team** that focuses on improving the infrastructure that empowers millions of customers to seamlessly manage their finances across borders. Here you will help the team address friction in adopting and using features such as USD local account details (that help customers receive USD to their Wise account) and interest/assets (that help customers earn a return on money held with Wise).

**In this role, you will:**

* Collaborate cross\\-functionally to shape and build our product
* Carry out data analysis using various statistical methods and tools to help us prioritise the most significant changes. All with the help of other senior analysts that will support you during your journey
* Collaborate with other stakeholders in the team and have the opportunity to share your ideas, working on projects that will be the most impactful for our customers

 **Qualifications*** **You are graduating in 2024 or 2025** with a Bachelors or Masters degree potentially in Data Science/Analytics, Computer Science, STEM or Economics/Business/Finance. However, a degree in a technical field is not a must as our selection process prioritises your skills.
* **Ready to start a full\\-time role on the 1st of September 2025\\.**
* You enjoy using numbers and data visualisation to tell a story
* You used coding to solve problems before and have some experience with using **SQL, Python, R.** That could be during your studies or as part of a personal project you’re passionate about!
* You’re **curious, keen to learn** and proactive by nature
* You’re **open to and value feedback** in order to improve
* Don’t worry, we don’t expect you to know everything!
* **Eligible to work in the US without any sponsorship** (now or in the future \\- please note that we can only move forward with people who are either US citizens or Green card holders.)
* Available to work in our local Austin office at least twice per week to support your development

 **Additional Information**  

You will have flexibility in how and where you work. We understand everyone needs a little something different \\- so we’ll do our best to make it happen, but we recommend coming to the office as much as possible in your first weeks!  

Gross salary of $95,000/year  

Fun and creative offices with social activities  

Be part of a global team with a global mindset.  

Have a real impact. Solve real customer problems.  

  

For more details on location\\-specific benefits, please check here.


For everyone, everywhere. We're people building money without borders — without judgement or prejudice, too. We believe teams are strongest when they are diverse, equitable and inclusive.


We're proud to have a truly international team, and we celebrate our differences.  

Inclusive teams help us live our values and make sure every Wiser feels respected, empowered to contribute towards our mission and able to progress in their careers.


If you want to find out more about what it's like to work at Wise visit Wise.Jobs.


Keep up to date with life at Wise by following us on LinkedIn and Instagram.

title: DevOps/SRE Engineer, Security Gov Cloud
description:
The application window is expected to close on: February 28, 2025\\.  

*Job posting may be removed earlier if the position is filled or if a sufficient number of applications are received.*  

Please Note: The successful applicant will be performing work on US Government classified environments, and therefore, must be a U.S. Person (i.e., U.S. citizen, U.S. national, lawful permanent resident, asylee, or refugee). This position may also perform work that the U.S. government has specified can only be performed by a U.S. citizen on U.S. soil.  

  

Preference will be given to candidates located near Cisco hub offices in Austin TX, Raleigh NC and Fulton MD. **Who We Are**
Cisco Systems is offering an extraordinary opportunity to be part of a small, innovative team with a low process, high throughput culture. The team is working on Cisco Defense Orchestrator, Secure Firewall Migration Tool, cloud\\-delivered Cisco Secure Dynamic Attributes Connector and cloud\\-delivered Firewall Management Center which manages policy and configuration of Security Business Group's firewalls. We are looking for a DevOps Engineer to contribute to all parts of our infrastructure stack in both Government and Commercial clouds.  

**Who you’ll work with**
In this role, you will be part of a passionate multi\\-functional team that builds and improves our suite of offerings under Cisco Security Cloud. Our agile team is responsible for the design and deployment of end\\-to\\-end solutions/software for Firewall Policy use cases, Dynamic Objects using CSDAC and Firewall Configuration Migration use cases, implement CI/CD features and fix bugs as well as improving the DevOps processes in response to feedback. **What you’ll do**The DevOps Engineer is responsible for the production process, including continuous delivery of features, infrastructure automation, configuration management, high availability, and related tooling. You will interact with cross functional team members across Cisco (Architects, Product Owners, Product Managers) to review designs and arrive at suitable design and contribute to development and testing. You’ll ensure software is deployed and operated to the highest quality through reliable monitoring using observability tools.
Additional responsibilities include:
* Participate as a technical contributor on a fast\\-paced project team of engineers involved in the development of SaaS security products.
* Contribute to continously evolve cloud infrastructure, making it more resilient, scalable, and secure.
* Automate all manual procedures.
* Partner with the engineering organization to converge on common infrastructure setup, tooling, and deployment processes.
* Research and recommend technologies to help further product goals.
* Respond to and resolve infrastructure related critical issues.
* Manage and participate in on\\-call rotation, rotated through engineering team
* Collaborate with the greater Cisco technical support team

 **Minimum Qualifications*** BS/CS or related STEM degree with 7\\+ years of professional technical experience to include 5 years of DevOps related tasks in a SaaS environment that is hosted in AWS
* 5\\+ years of work within Linux based systems including use of Bash or related scripting languages (Example: General purpose language such as Ruby/Python).
* 3\\+ years of experience in the design, deployment, and operation of Kubernetes (AWS EKS) clusters and workloads.
* 4\\+ years of work with infrastructure automation tools such as Terraform, Ansible and CloudFormation
* 3\\+ years of setting up, configuring, maintaining, and evolving a CI/CD environment using tools such as Jenkins/Argo CD/TeamCity/Bamboo/etc.

 **Preferred Qualifications*** Create and manage a safe deployment procedure of new product changes across multiple environments (preferably backup/restore, secure credentials at rest like Vault);
* Ability to build SaaS monitoring solutions that detect and automatically remediate system faults (e.g. Datadog, Splunk)
* Triage, Debug and troubleshoot in a distributed environment.
* Understanding on computer system and network security.
* Agile software development.
* Collaboration skills, to reach out and triage critical issues in production that could be Priority 1, Priority 2

  

\\#WeAreCisco


\\#WeAreCisco where every individual brings their unique skills and perspectives together to pursue our purpose of powering an inclusive future for all.


Our passion is connection\\-we celebrate our employees' diverse set of backgrounds and focus on unlocking potential. Cisconians often experience one company, many careers where learning and development are encouraged and supported at every stage. Our


technology, tools, and culture pioneered hybrid work trends, allowing all to not only give their best, but be their best.

Dedicated paid time off to volunteer\\-80 hours each year\\-allows us to give back to causes we are passionate about, and nearly 86% do!


Our purpose, driven by our people, is what makes us the worldwide leader in technology that powers the internet. Helping our customers reimagine their applications, secure their enterprise, transform their infrastructure, and meet their sustainability goals is what we do best. We ensure that every step we take is a step towards a more inclusive future for all. Take your next step and be you, with us!


  
**Message to applicants applying to work in the U.S. and/or Canada:**  

  

When available, the salary range posted for this position reflects the projected hiring range for new hire, full\\-time salaries in U.S. and/or Canada locations, not including equity or benefits. For non\\-sales roles the hiring ranges reflect base salary only; employees are also eligible to receive annual bonuses. Hiring ranges for sales positions include base and incentive compensation target. Individual pay is determined by the candidate's hiring location and additional factors, including but not limited to skillset, experience, and relevant education, certifications, or training. Applicants may not be eligible for the full salary range based on their U.S. or Canada hiring location. The recruiter can share more details about compensation for the role in your location during the hiring process.
U.S. employees have **access** to quality medical, dental and vision insurance, a 401(k) plan with a Cisco matching contribution, short and long\\-term disability coverage, basic life insurance and numerous wellbeing offerings.


Employees receive up to twelve paid holidays per calendar year, which includes one floating holiday (for non\\-exempt employees), plus a day off for their birthday. Non\\-Exempt new hires accrue up to 16 days of vacation time off each year, at a rate of 4\\.92 hours per pay period. Exempt new hires participate in Cisco’s flexible Vacation Time Off policy, which does not place a defined limit on how much vacation time eligible employees may use, but is subject to availability and some business limitations. All new hires are eligible for Sick Time Off subject to Cisco’s Sick Time Off Policy and will have eighty (80\\) hours of sick time off provided on their hire date and on January 1st of each year thereafter. Up to 80 hours of unused sick time will be carried forward from one calendar year to the next such that the maximum number of sick time hours an employee may have available is 160 hours. Employees in Illinois have a unique time off program designed specifically with local requirements in mind. All employees also have access to paid time away to deal with critical or emergency issues. We offer additional paid time to volunteer and give back to the community.


Employees on sales plans earn performance\\-based incentive pay on top of their base salary, which is split between quota and non\\-quota components. For quota\\-based incentive pay, Cisco typically pays as follows:


.75% of incentive target for each 1% of revenue attainment up to 50% of quota;


1\\.5% of incentive target for each 1% of attainment between 50% and 75%;


1% of incentive target for each 1% of attainment between 75% and 100%; and once performance exceeds 100% attainment, incentive rates are at or above 1% for each 1% of attainment with no cap on incentive compensation.


For non\\-quota\\-based sales performance elements such as strategic sales objectives, Cisco may pay up to 125% of target. Cisco sales plans do not have a minimum threshold of performance for sales incentive compensation to be paid.

title: PRINCIPAL SOFTWARE ENGINEER
description:
**WHO WE ARE**


Founded in 2018, Zogo has been on a remarkable journey in financial education. Over the years, we've had the privilege of partnering with 250 financial institutions and assembling a dedicated team of passionate and skilled team members. Our impact is something we're incredibly proud of, with a user\\-base that has grown to over 1\\.5M people who have diligently completed more than 10 million education modules. At Zogo, we want everyone to be empowered to reach their financial goals — and we need your help to make it happen.

**ABOUT THIS ROLE**


Zogo is currently seeking a technical leader, strategist, and hands\\-on contributor as a Principal Engineer to join our team in Austin, Texas. Our products include an iOS/Android application, web products and various integrations, and we are looking for someone to lead a team designing and developing our core software products. You will work closely with cross\\-functional teams, including product, design, and IT, to deliver scalable and impactful solutions. This role demands a deep technical expertise, innovative thinking, ability to lead and contribute in setting good code standards and a passion for mentoring teams in a scrappy startup environment.


This is a great opportunity to join an established yet expanding fintech company that is revolutionizing financial education as we know it.

**Who you are:**

* Passionate about quality and technology with a strong commitment to excellence.
* Creative problem\\-solver with a keen eye for detail.
* Strong communicator who can work collaboratively across different teams.
* Adaptable and open to change in a fast\\-paced environment.
* Self\\-motivated and capable of working independently or leading a team.
* Experience in fintech or building software for financial education.
* Familiarity with data analytics, machine learning, or personalization algorithms.
* Background in engineering best practices, particularly in managing sensitive data and mobile app integrations.

**You'll be responsible for:**


Technical Leadership

* Define and drive the overall technical strategy, architecture and performance of systems through thoughtful design and best practices.
* Evaluate and integrate cutting\\-edge technologies and tools to enhance the development process.


Hands\\-On Development

* Write high\\-quality, maintainable code and set coding standards for the engineering team.
* Lead by example in solving complex technical challenges and debugging critical issues.
* Collaborate with engineering teams to deliver features on time and with a high level of quality.


Mentorship and Collaboration

* Mentor and guide engineers, fostering a culture of learning and innovation.
* Facilitate technical discussions, code reviews, and knowledge\\-sharing sessions.
* Act as a trusted advisor for both technical and non\\-technical stakeholders.


Product Innovation

* Translate user needs and financial literacy concepts into intuitive and impactful software solutions.
* Contribute to brainstorming sessions and prototypes to test new ideas.


Operational Excellence

* Ensure robust CI/CD pipelines and deployment processes are in place.
* Define and track KPIs for system performance and reliability.
* Oversee incident management and guide teams in post\\-mortem analysis to improve systems.

**YOUR EXPERIENCE:**

* Deep understanding of cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) and microservices architecture.
* Experience with scalable systems, distributed systems, and API design.
* Proven track record of delivering complex software projects in a fast\\-paced environment.

* Passion for financial literacy and a desire to make a meaningful impact.
* Experience with mobile app development (Kotlin and/or Swift)
* Native SDK development experience is a plus
* Relevant qualification or degree in Computer Science or related field is preferred.


\\#ZOGO

**OUR REWARDS**


We offer a robust package of employee perks and benefits, including healthcare benefits (medical, dental and vision, EAP), competitive PTO, 401k match, parental leave, and HSA contribution match. We also provide our employees with a paid subscription to the Calm app and offer generous external learning and tuition reimbursement benefits. As a hybrid workforce, we offer our employees the ability to work remotely up to two days a week.

title: Principal Software Engineer
description:
Favor’s mission is ‘Anything Delivered.' Our engineers make high\\-touch logistics happen. The Favor technology platform is the engine behind the business, enabling millions of Favors. Our technology efficiently manages the real\\-time assignment of Runners to Favors, facilitates communication between customers, Runners, and support, keeps thousands of customer and Runner mobile applications in sync, and more.  

Do you get a thrill when you impact hundreds of thousands of users? Do you want to work for a purpose\\-driven, value\\-driven company in a high\\-growth environment? Our engineers create the tools and applications to connect our customers, Runners, merchants, and support teams. You will work closely with our product and operations teams to understand customer needs, build simple solutions to complex problems, and deliver delightful experiences to all our users.  

At Favor, we are committed to building a world\\-class team that shares a passion for modern, clean code and products that make a difference. We need engineers like you to help us achieve our mission of ‘Anything Delivered.’ As a Principal Software Engineer at Favor you will be responsible for all phases of development, testing, and deployment of our applications.
### **What you'll do:**

* + Champion best practices and scalable architectural patterns, enabling engineers to drive adoption across the org for a maintainable and reliable codebase.
	+ Lead and drive large\\-scale technical initiatives, balancing short\\-term practical needs with long\\-term architectural vision while securing buy\\-in from engineers and leadership.
	+ Eliminate barriers to scale through technology and process and provide building blocks of world\\-class applications and services.
	+ Influence across disciplines, cross\\-functional teams, and leadership, effectively bridging technical and business considerations.
	+ Serve as a mentor and technical leader, fostering growth in engineers and raising the overall technical bar through coaching and shared expertise.

### **Skills you have:**

* + A relevant degree or equivalent work experience with 15\\+ years in software engineering.
	+ Proven ability to lead large, cross\\-functional initiatives, collaborating effectively with product, design, and engineering teams.
	+ Strong technical influence shapes engineering direction, defines quality standards, and drives best practices to ensure engineering excellence.
	+ Deep expertise in software design patterns, enabling the development of clean, well\\-structured, and idiomatic code that fully leverages modern programming language.
	+ Ability to architect and write scalable, efficient solutions using advanced algorithms and data structures, optimizing for various technical and business constraints.
	+ Expertise in test automation, observability, and debugging strategies to ensure software reliability and maintainability.
	+ Strong understanding of data engineering principles, ensuring effective data processing, storage, and scalability.
	+ Strong knowledge of security best practices, proactively addressing vulnerabilities and designing secure systems.
	+ Ability to navigate ambiguity, drive problems from conception to resolution, and advocate for solutions with a strong sense of ownership.
	+ Ability to communicate difficult technical concepts in precise, concise, and unambiguous terms.

### **Who you are:**

* + Appreciate simple design.
	+ Enjoy implementing robust engineering strategies, including best logging, tracing, and troubleshooting practices to improve observability and reliability.
	+ Will take ownership during critical incidents, working with on\\-call teams to diagnose and resolve complex production issues swiftly and effectively.
	+ A proven leader who identifies areas needing engineering direction and sees them through to impactful solutions.
	+ Can write clean, well\\-tested code in your sleep, with a test\\-first mindset.
	+ Very well\\-versed in Domain Driven Design.
	+ Enjoy working with other engineers in a collaborative and iterative environment.
	+ Communicate well with technical and non\\-technical stakeholders.
	+ Experience or familiarity with one or more of the following technologies: JVM\\-based languages, PHP, MySQL, Postgres, DynamoDB, NoSQL, Kafka, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, AWS, Elasticsearch.

**Life at Favor** **Where you’ll work:** This is a hybrid role, meaning you’ll work from home roughly three days per week and collaborate with other team members in person at our HQ in Austin, Texas for the remaining work days. No matter where you work best, we foster an inclusive and flexible environment to support our workforce. **Benefits**: We offer premium health, vision, dental, and life insurance, alongside 401(k) options. We go beyond the basics, while also throwing in Favor delivery fee credit and H\\-E\\-B discounts! **Paid time off (PTO):** We offer unlimited PTO for salaried employees (that’s actually unlimited) and ample vacation time to all team members. **Learning and development:** We encourage personal growth and education through Intern(al)ships and Learning Labs taught by Favor team members and external facilitators. **Community**: Whether you’re an avid cyclist, dog lover, or Magic enthusiast, there’s a group for you here.
