title: Sr. Construction Estimator
description:
**Role: Senior Construction Estimator** 




**Join Us:** 




 We are a consulting firm providing estimates, schedules, cost analysis, program/project controls and technology expertise to both public and private sectors. We mentor the best people, provide them with the very best practice knowledge and technology, and commit ourselves to achieve exemplary project results.
 



**Purpose:** 




 The Senior Construction Estimator typically collaborates with a project team that is part of the owner organization, stakeholders, project management, and A/E to help leaders determine what they need to see a project through to completion.
 **They evaluate relative costs or potential risks and conclude whether they can complete a project within the time frame and budget that the client has or wants to establish.** 




**Duties, Functions and Responsibilities** 
 :
 



 Reads and interprets construction documents and specifications developed by Architects and Engineers (A/Es) that are
 **15%** 
 complete or better. From this and project information coordinated by the Chief Estimator and Estimating Manager, he or she develops an organizational scheme using Construction Specification Institutes (CSI) divisional categories
 **and Uniformat systems for early design stage estimates** 
 . Quantity takeoff (QTO) measurements of construction scope using scaled units of measure (UOM) that correlate to itemized pricing for labor, material, and construction equipment are organized by CSI. title: Commissioning Engineer
description:
**Joining Arup** 

 Arup's purpose, shared values, and collaborative approach has set us apart for over 75 years, guiding how we shape a better world.
 



 We are seeking a Commissioning Engineer to join our Austin office. The commissioning team leads all aspects of the quality assurance and solving tasks for engineered systems in the built environment. Commissioning in accordance with ASHRAE and other international guidelines are applied to guide Arup's World\\-Class approach to commissioning. We are involved in four major types of the commissioning projects, Commissioning, Retro\\-Commissioning, Re\\-Commissioning, and Continuous Commissioning. Our team focuses on operational improvements for existing facilities, using commissioning techniques to analyze and implement better building controls and energy systems.
 


**The opportunity** 
* Develop strong interpersonal and communication skills crucial for team\\-based work.
* Develop commissioning documentation under the mentorship of the Lead Commissioning Engineer.
* Understand commissioning best practices as ASHRAE, BxCA, AEE, NFPA etc.
* Assisting the Lead Commissioning Engineer in developing and implementing testing procedures during the acceptance phase of construction.
* Analyze system performance utilizing historical data, site measurements, and trending.
* Develop spreadsheets for analyses, perform field assessments and on\\-site commissioning activities.
* Deploy metering/monitoring devices for assessment of systems.
* Develop presentations to translate analysis findings, or specific stages of the commissioning process.
* Shadow/learn different internal design disciplines to understand the design process from the innovative eyes of Arup designers, planners, and engineers.
* Develop an understanding of high\\-performance design, test \\& balance, control strategy optimization, energy efficient equipment design, and life cycle costing.
* Develop an understanding of mechanical, electrical, lighting, plumbing, facades, fire/life safety, and building controls systems.
* Work with the lead Commissioning engineer to learn client control systems, identify system shortfalls, and analyze for alternatives.
* Prepare summaries of work for clients, attend client meetings, and assist with proposal development.
* Cost \\& benefit analysis of improvement measures over a project life cycle.
* Working with Lead Commissioning Engineer to optimize control strategies for MEP systems.
* Develop an understanding of commissioning tasks associated with LEED \\& WELL projects.
* Develop an understanding of ASHRAE energy audits.
* Develop understanding of project documentation such as scope of work, specifications, submittals, design drawings, RFI's, O\\&M's, and systems manuals.



 You will have the opportunity to do socially useful work that has meaning \\- to Arup, to your career, to our members and to the clients and communities we serve.
 



**Is this role right for you?** 



**Qualifications** 
* Bachelor's degree \\- Engineering, Architectural Engineering, Environmental Science and/ or related technical fields.
* Minimum 4 years of professional experience of HVAC and controls experience in design, construction, energy evaluation and Commissioning.
* Effective interpersonal skills.
* Outstanding analytical problem\\-solving skills.
* Must have a passion to learn and enjoy collaborating with a team.
* Desire to work at desk and in field.
* Understanding of energy, and water system technologies inside buildings.
* Excellent interpersonal and digital literacy.
* Familiarity with triple bottom line cost\\-effectiveness analysis.
* Working towards Commissioning or related credentials a plus.
* Knowledge of building automation systems a plus.
* Experience with Controls, and Test \\& Balance of building systems a plus.
* Must not now, nor in the future require visa sponsorship to maintain work authorization.


**Notable Projects:** 

 For over seven decades Arup has been at the forefront of the most ambitious and innovative design and engineering. From concert halls to national stadiums, renewable energy to policy change, we continue to add to that history every day. Notable projects from our Commissioning team include:
 


* Child Safe San Antonio
* Houston Methodist
* Various Texas Airports
* WeWork Facilities
* Texas State University
* CHI St. Luke's
* And more...



 Please note that all applicants must apply directly via the job portal. If this role is not quite what you are looking for, but you are interested in other opportunities for a future with purpose, please sign up to our Talent Community where you will be kept up to date with roles suitable for you to shape a better world.
 


**What we offer you** 

 At Arup, we care about each member's success, so we can grow together.
 



 Guided by our values, we provide an attractive total reward package that recognizes the contribution of each of our members to our shared success. As well as competitive, fair and equitable pay, we offer a career in which all of our members can belong, grow and thrive \\- through benefits that support health and wellbeing, a wide range of learning opportunities and many possibilities to have an impact through the work they do.
 



 We are owned in trust on behalf of our members, giving us the freedom, with personal responsibility, to set our own direction and choose work that aligns with our purpose and adds to Arup's legacy. Our members collaborate on ambitious projects to deliver remarkable outcomes for our clients and communities. Profit Share is a key part of our reward, enabling members to share in the results of our collective efforts.
 



**Benefits at Work** 
 \\- At Arup, we have a comprehensive and valuable benefits program that works for our employees and their families while keeping costs low. These benefits provide health and welfare security for you as well as paid time off for rest and renewal. As a member of Arup, everyone shares in our success through a global profit share scheme (payments are dependent on the firm's financial performance). Our Global Profit Share Plan (paid bi\\-annually) provides an opportunity for you to share in the success of the Firm. As a valued employee of Arup, you can also choose to participate in our 401(k) plan with up to 10% company match to help you save for your future
 



**Flexible Working** 
 \\- We believe that flexible arrangements create a more inclusive way of working that supports our diversity and the wellbeing of our people. Options for alternative schedules and the ability to work outside of the office for a portion of your workweek are available
 



**Austin** 
**Hiring Range** 
 \\- Hiring Range \\- The good faith base salary hiring range for this job if performed in Austin is $83,300 to $112,700 per year.
 **This range is commensurate with experience, educational background, and skill level.** 
 Benefits are not included in the base salary. Please note hiring ranges for candidates performing work outside of Austin will differ.
 


**Different People, Shared Values** 

 Arup is an equal opportunity employer that actively promotes and nurtures a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome applications from individuals of all backgrounds, regardless of age (within legal limits), gender identity or expression, marital status, disability, neurotype or mental health, race or ethnicity, faith or belief, sexual orientation, socioeconomic background, and whether you're pregnant or on family leave. We are an open environment that embraces diverse experiences, perspectives, and ideas \\- this drives our excellence.
 



 Guided by our values and alignment with the UN Sustainable Development Goals, we create and contribute to equitable spaces and systems, while cultivating a sense of belonging for all. Our internal employee networks support our inclusive culture: from race, ethnicity and cross\\-cultural working to gender equity and LGBTQ\\+ and disability inclusion \\- we aim to create a space for you to express yourself and make a positive difference. Discover more about life at Arup at www.arup.com/careers/your\\-life\\-at\\-arup.
 


**Our Application Process** 

 We will be reviewing our candidates for this position on a rolling basis. Once you have applied you will be evaluated and potentially moved on to the next round, at which point a member of the talent resourcing team will reach out to you directly.
 



**Arup is an equal opportunity employer.** 
 All qualified applicants will receive consideration without regard to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, spouse of a protected veteran, or disability.
 



**Stay safe online.** 
 Recruitment fraud is on the rise, and Arup's name, logo, and branding have been used in fraudulent job advertisements. Arup will never ask for bank information as part of our recruitment process.

 Whether people and businesses are sending money to another country, spending abroad, or making and receiving international payments, Wise is on a mission to make their lives easier and save them money.
 



 As part of our team, you will be helping us create an entirely new network for the world's money.
   

**For everyone, everywhere.** 




 More about
 **our mission** 
 and
 **what we offer** 
 .
 


 Job Description
   

  


**Role/Programme:** 
  

  

 As an Analytics Intern, you’ll join our Analytics team in the summer for 10 weeks in the summer (3rd June \\- 8th August 2025\\). During this time, you will work on 1\\-2 Analytical projects and use them to propose your own ideas to take your team further, doing what’s best for our customers.
 



**You'll be a part of the Regional North America Analytics squad where you will:** 



* Be a strategy partner to Regional North America product managers and engineers to help shape the future of the North America Wise product
* Collaborate with cross\\-functional teams, including product managers, engineers, bankers, as well as global analytics teams, to foster innovative solutions and gain a comprehensive understanding of the product.
* Assist in building and optimizing data infrastructure and pipelines using tools like dBt, Snowflake, Looker, and Superset that support strategic, data\\-driven decisions for the team.



 We are looking for 2 interns to join us for the programme in Austin, so y
 **ou’ll be a part of one of the following teams:** 



* **NorthAm Verification team:** 
 to understand and enhance KYC/KYB (Know Your Customer / Know Your Business) experience for customers. Here you will identify and address customer pain points in the verification funnel, contributing strategies to streamline the onboarding process and enhance user experience.
* **NorthAm Wise Account team:** 
 to improve the infrastructure that empowers millions of customers to seamlessly manage their finances across borders. Here you will help the team address friction in adopting and using features such as USD local account details (that help customers receive USD to their Wise account) and interest/assets (that help customers earn a return on money held with Wise).



**In this role, you will:** 



* Collaborate cross\\-functionally to shape and build our product
* Carry out data analysis using various statistical methods and tools to help us prioritise the most significant changes. All with the help of other senior analysts that will support you during your journey
* Collaborate with other stakeholders in the team and have the opportunity to share your ideas, working on projects that will be the most impactful for our customers


 Qualifications
   

  

* You are a
 **penultimate or final year student (graduating in 2025 or 2026\\)** 
 from a Bachelors or Masters degree potentially in Data Science/Analytics, Computer Science, STEM or Economics/Business/Finance. However, a degree in a technical field is not a must as our selection process prioritises your skills.
* You are
 **able to start a 10 weeks internship from 3 June**
* You enjoy using numbers and data visualisation to tell a story
* You used coding to solve problems before and have some experience with using
 **SQL, Python, R.** 
 That could be during your studies or as part of a personal project you’re passionate about!
* You’re
 **curious, keen to learn and proactive** 
 by nature
* You’re open to and value feedback in order to improve
* Don’t worry, we don’t expect you to know everything!
* **Eligible to work in the US  without any sponsorship** 
 (now or in the future \\- please note that we can only move forward with people who are either US citizens or Green card holders.)
* Available to work in our local Austin office at least twice per week to support your development


  

  

 Additional Information
   

  


 You will have flexibility in how and where you work. We understand everyone needs a little something different \\- so we’ll do our best to make it happen, but we recommend coming to the office as much as possible in your first weeks!
   

 Gross salary of $76,000/year (pro\\-rata)
   

 Fun and creative offices with social activities
   

 Be part of a global team with a global mindset.
   

 Have a real impact. Solve real customer problems.
   

  

 For more details on location\\-specific benefits, please check here.
 





 For everyone, everywhere. We're people building money without borders  — without judgement or prejudice, too. We believe teams are strongest when they are diverse, equitable and inclusive.
 



 We're proud to have a truly international team, and we celebrate our differences.
   

 Inclusive teams help us live our values and make sure every Wiser feels respected, empowered to contribute towards our mission and able to progress in their careers.
 



 If you want to find out more about what it's like to work at Wise visit Wise.Jobs.
 



 Keep up to date with life at Wise by following us on LinkedIn and Instagram.

title: ASIC Engineer, Methodology
description:
Meta is hiring ASIC Methodology Engineers within our Infrastructure organization to work on design integrity and signoff methodology development. We are looking for individuals with experience in timing signoff flow/methodology development for large complex disaggregated ASICs, with exposure to library characterization, STA, modeling, extraction, variation analysis, aging, and signoff flows to build efficient System on Chip (SoC) and IP for data center applications. ASIC Engineer, Methodology Responsibilities Work with our ASIC vendor partners and Foundries to assess signoff margins and tradeoffs at design/arch/process\\-tech levels and drive PPA and design integrity for Meta SOCs.
 



 Develop Meta's internal timing signoff methods and flows, establishing signoff policy, timing corners, extraction, aging, and reliability metrics, for IP and SOC, from synthesis to Tape Out. Define and develop checklists and audits for IP and SOC development milestones including TO, from a timing signoff perspective. Develop robust timing signoff automation and test structures to ensure Meta's timing methodology is A0\\-production ready.
 



 Drive test\\-chip/IP methodologies as necessary to update Meta's signoff requirements for new process technologies. Partner with EDA tool vendors to select and deploy the appropriate timing signoff features and flows to improve productivity and ensure design integrity. Minimum Qualifications Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, relevant technical field, or equivalent practical experience.
 



 12\\+ years of experience with STA, modeling, signoff methodology development, variation analysis, etc. Experience with EDA tools and scripting languages (Python, Tcl) used to build tools and flows for complex environments. Preferred Qualifications Experience with library characterization, process technology evaluation, and test chip development for better understanding of process technology across multiple nodes/foundries.
 



 Experience with aging and reliability methodologies, and associated flow development. Experience with IP modeling and integration into SOC from a timing/signoff perspective. Experience with Post\\-silicon bring\\-up, debug and identify any process/timing related issues.
 



 Experience managing multiple design releases and working with cross functional teams to support and debug timing signoff issues. Experience with communicating across functional internal teams and with vendors Knowledge of front\\-end and back\\-end ASIC tools. Experience with RTL design using SystemVerilog or other HDL.
 



 For those who live in or expect to work from California if hired for this position, please click here for additional information. About Meta Meta builds technologies that help people connect, find communities, and grow businesses. When Facebook launched in 2004, it changed the way people connect.
 



 Apps like Messenger, Instagram and WhatsApp further empowered billions around the world. Now, Meta is moving beyond 2D screens toward immersive experiences like augmented and virtual reality to help build the next evolution in social technology. People who choose to build their careers by building with us at Meta help shape a future that will take us beyond what digital connection makes possible today\\-beyond the constraints of screens, the limits of distance, and even the rules of physics.
 



 $212,000/year to $291,000/year \\+ bonus \\+ equity \\+ benefits Individual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base hourly rate, monthly rate, or annual salary only, and do not include bonus, equity or sales incentives, if applicable. In addition to base compensation, Meta offers benefits.
 



 Learn more about benefits at Meta. Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action Meta is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. title: Directional Drilling Manager - Communications
description:
**Key Responsibilities** 
**1\\. Project Planning and Coordination** 
* Assess project requirements, blueprints, and technical specifications.
* Develop comprehensive drilling plans, including bore paths, site layouts, and material requirements.
* Collaborate with clients, project managers, and engineers to align on project goals, deliverables, and timelines.


**2\\. Equipment and Resource Management** 
* Select appropriate drilling equipment and ensure proper maintenance for optimal performance.
* Oversee mobilization and demobilization of drilling rigs and other resources.
* Manage the inventory of drilling tools, fluids, and other consumables to prevent delays.


**3\\. Team Leadership** 
* Supervise drilling crews, foremen, and subcontractors to ensure operational efficiency.
* Provide training and support to enhance team skills and enforce safe working practices.
* Evaluate team performance, address skill gaps, and resolve inefficiencies.


**4\\. Operational Oversight** 
* Monitor drilling operations to ensure adherence to project plans, budgets, and timelines.
* Troubleshoot and resolve issues such as equipment malfunctions, bore path deviations, or unexpected subsurface conditions.
* Utilize and interpret steering tools, sensors, and logging systems to guide drilling operations accurately.


**5\\. Safety and Compliance** 
* Enforce safety protocols and conduct regular safety meetings and drills.
* Ensure full compliance with local, state, and federal regulations related to drilling and environmental protection.
* Investigate and address any incidents or near\\-misses on\\-site to prevent recurrence.


**6\\. Technical Expertise and Problem\\-Solving** 
* Analyze geological data to identify potential risks or challenges.
* Optimize drilling techniques to improve efficiency and accuracy.
* Evaluate and implement new technologies or methods to enhance operational performance.


**7\\. Quality Assurance** 
* Ensure accuracy in bore paths and successful installation of conduits or pipelines.
* Conduct quality checks to meet client expectations and regulatory standards.
* Address issues related to alignment, depth, or material integrity promptly.


**8\\. Environmental Considerations** 
* Minimize environmental impact through responsible drilling practices.
* Oversee the disposal of drilling mud and waste materials in compliance with environmental regulations.


**Key Skills and Qualifications** 
* Strong knowledge of HDD equipment, techniques, and operations.
* Ability to read and interpret construction blueprints, technical drawings, and utility maps.
* Proficiency with directional drilling software and tracking systems.
* Leadership and communication skills to effectively manage teams and coordinate with clients.
* Strong problem\\-solving abilities to address on\\-site challenges.
* Comprehensive understanding of safety and environmental regulations.

title: Cloud Operations Lead - Kubernetes, Charles River Development, Assistant Vice President
description:
**Who we are looking for** 




 Charles River Development is looking for an experiencedCloud Native Operations Lead. The successful candidate will be responsible for automating and streamlining our operations and processes, building and maintaining tools for deployment, monitoring, and operations as well as troubleshooting and resolving issues in our development, test, and production environments. Our ideal candidate is proficient with Kubernetes, container orchestration, CI/CD pipelines, and cloud platforms. They should also be familiar with the software development lifecycle and have a deep understanding of modern DevOps tools and practices.
 







**Why this role is important to us** 




 The team you will be joining is a part of Charles River Development (or CRD), that became a part of State Street in 2018\\. CRD helps create enterprise investment management software solutions for large institutions in the areas of institutional investment, wealth management and hedge funds. Together we have created first open front\\-to\\-back platform \\- State Street Alpha, that was launched in 2019\\.
 



 Join us if delivering next generation infrastructure, using emerging technologies like AI and Blockchain sounds like a challenge you are up for.
 







**What you will be responsible for** 




 As a Cloud Platform Engineer, you will:
 


* Operate and maintain the Kubernetes platform for container orchestration
* Work closely with development teams to architect and implement applications in a scalable and resilient manner
* Ensure the reliability, scalability, and security of the platform and applications
* Perform day\\-to\\-day operational tasks such as upgrades and patching of Kubernetes platform
* Automate operational tasks using scripting languages such as Python, Bash or Shell
* Develop and implement CI/CD pipelines for application deployment on Kubernetes
* Monitor the health of the platform and applications using tools like Prometheus, Grafana or ELK stack
* Assist with capacity planning and load testing of the platform and applications
* Develop and enforce best practices for building container\\-based applications
* Troubleshoot issues within the platform and work with development teams to resolve application issues
* Stay updated with the latest industry trends and technologies in container orchestration and cloud\\-native development
* 
* 
* 



**What we value** 



* Applied expertise in designing/implementing secure platforms for applications and data
* Thorough understanding of both Windows and Linux\\-based infrastructure
* A passion for learning about emerging technologies and sharing knowledge
* Experience documenting technology standards, operational procedures, and requirements







**Education \\& Preferred Qualifications** 



* Proven work experience as a Kubernetes Platform Engineer or similar role in DevOps
* Deep knowledge of Kubernetes and Docker
* Experience with Azure cloud platform
* Experience with Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools like Terraform
* Familiarity with CI/CD tools like Argocd , jenkins etc
* Experience with monitoring tools like Prometheus , Grafana , ELK stack etc
* Strong scripting skills (Python, Bash, etc.)
* Ability to troubleshoot complex networking issues
* BS degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related field











**Additional requirements** 




 Work experience in multiple public clouds preferred
 







**About State Street** 




**What we do.** 
 State Street is one of the largest custodian banks, asset managers and asset intelligence companies in the world. From technology to product innovation, we're making our mark on the financial services industry. For more than two centuries, we've been helping our clients safeguard and steward the investments of millions of people. We provide investment servicing, data \\& analytics, investment research \\& trading and investment management to institutional clients.
 



**Work, Live and Grow.** 
 We make all efforts to create a great work environment. Our benefits packages are competitive and comprehensive. Details vary by location, but you may expect generous medical care, insurance and savings plans, among other perks. You'll have access to flexible Work Programs to help you match your needs. And our wealth of development programs and educational support will help you reach your full potential.
 



**Inclusion, Diversity and Social Responsibility.** 
 We truly believe our employees' diverse backgrounds, experiences and perspectives are a powerful contributor to creating an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive and reach their maximum potential while adding value to both our organization and our clients. We warmly welcome candidates of diverse origin, background, ability, age, sexual orientation, gender identity and personality. Another fundamental value at State Street is active engagement with our communities around the world, both as a partner and a leader. You will have tools to help balance your professional and personal life, paid volunteer days, matching gift programs and access to employee networks that help you stay connected to what matters to you.
 



 State Street is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer.
 



*Company: Charles River Development* 








**Salary Range:** 



 $100,000 \\- $160,000 Annual
 




 The range quoted above applies to the role in the primary location specified. If the candidate would ultimately work outside of the primary location above, the applicable range could differ.
 







**Job Application Disclosure:** 




 It is unlawful in Massachusetts to require or administer a lie detector test as a condition of employment or continued employment. An employer who violates this law shall be subject to criminal penalties and civil liability.

* Understanding of security principles and best practices in web application development.

title: Enterprise Inside Sales Representative
description:
Job Description
   

  


 We’re looking for an
 **Enterprise Inside Sales Representative** 
 to join Procore’s Sales team. In this role, you’ll partner with our Account Executives and Sales Engineers to support the entire sales lifecycle for new and existing enterprise businesses comprising top global Fortune 500 companies. 
 



 As an Enterprise Inside Sales Representative and expert resource to our Enterprise Account Executives, you’ll run deals independently while staying in close communication with the Sales team.  You’ll supplement sales and networking abilities with technical knowledge of cloud\\-based software and Procore platform expertise. If you’re looking for the opportunity to join a highly collaborative and rapidly growing sales organization—we have a spot for you on our team.
 



 This position reports to the Sr. Manager of Inside Sales Representatives and can be based in our Carpinteria, CA, Austin, TX, or Tampa, FL offices. We’re looking for someone to join us immediately.
 



**What You’ll Do:** 



* Generate a healthy "Run Rate" business within your strategic segment. "Run Rate" comprises product line cross\\-sell, upsell, and contract expansion into current clients, and initial "Land \\& Expand" deals with separate business units or subsidiaries of large prospects
* Build relationships with construction management C\\-Suite, leaders, and critical decision\\-makers by visiting clients and prospects,  serving as their front end point of contact
* Work in close partnership with Sales Development Reps and Strategic Account Executives to support pre\\-sales efforts with prospects and partners
* Participate in presentations and onsite meetings, coordinate RFPs, and position Procore as the leading construction software solution to prospects
* Work with Field Sales team to close new business by addressing prospects’ technical challenges
* Set up Enterprise Account Executives for success by building awareness and interest within the prospect’s organization
* Complete immersion and mastery of Procore’s product offerings, business model, services, and emerging technologies
* Provide fellow team members with mentoring and support
* Collaborate with all levels of the Procore organization to develop best practices, connect prospects and clients with Product Managers and Marketing to further client success and Procore’s evolution as a market leader
* Travel up to 25% to client sites, industry events, Procore offices, and more!



**What we’re looking for:** 




*Construction management experts looking to transition into a fast\\-paced software company:* 



* 1\\+ years of experience in the construction industry in a management role or as a Project Engineer, Project Manager, Assistant Project Manager, or Project Administrator is preferred

 Additional Information
   

  


 Base Pay Range $28 \\- $38 plus commission for an estimated on\\-target earnings of $96,600 \\- $132,825\\. This role is also eligible for Equity Compensation. Procore is committed to offering competitive, fair, and commensurate compensation, and has provided an estimated pay range for this role. Actual compensation will be based on a candidate’s job\\-related skills, experience, education or training, and location.
 





**Perks \\& Benefits** 




 At Procore, we invest in our employees and provide a full range of benefits and perks to help you grow and thrive. From generous paid time off and healthcare coverage to career enrichment and development programs, learn more details about what we offer and how we empower you to be your best.
 



**About Us** 




 Procore Technologies is building the software that builds the world. We provide cloud\\-based construction management software that helps clients more efficiently build skyscrapers, hospitals, retail centers, airports, housing complexes, and more. At Procore, we have worked hard to create and maintain a culture where you can own your work and are encouraged and given resources to try new ideas. Check us out on Glassdoor to see what others are saying about working at Procore.
 



 We are an equal\\-opportunity employer and welcome builders of all backgrounds. We thrive in a diverse, dynamic, and inclusive environment. We do not tolerate discrimination against candidates or employees on the basis of gender, sex, national origin, civil status, family status, sexual orientation, religion, age, disability, race, traveler community, status as a protected veteran or any other classification protected by law.
 



 If you'd like to stay in touch and be the first to hear about new roles at Procore, join our Talent Community.
 



 Alternative methods of applying for employment are available to individuals unable to submit an application through this site because of a disability. Contact our benefits team here to discuss reasonable accommodations.

 Procore will consider for employment all qualified applicants, including those with arrest or conviction records, in accordance with the requirements of applicable federal, state, and local laws, including the City of Los Angeles’ Fair Chance Initiative for Hiring Ordinance, the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance for Employers, and the California Fair Chance Act.
 



 A criminal history may have a direct, adverse, and negative relationship on the following job duties, potentially resulting in the withdrawal of the conditional offer of employment: 1\\. appropriately managing, accessing, and handling confidential information including proprietary and trade secret information, as well as accessing Procore's information technology systems and platforms; 2\\. interacting with and occasionally having unsupervised contact with internal/external customers, stakeholders, and/or colleagues; and 3\\. exercising sound judgment.

title: Senior Cybersecurity Engineer
description:
At first glance, you'll see Danaher's scale. Our 65,000\\+ associates work across the globe at more than 15 unique operating companies within three platforms\\-life sciences, diagnostics, and biotechnology.
 







 Look again and you'll see the opportunity to build a meaningful career, be creative, and take risks with the support you need to be successful. You'll find associates who are as certain about their impact as they are about where they're headed next.
 







 You'll find the Danaher Business System, which makes everything possible. You'll also see a company that investors trust\\-our culture of continuous improvement has helped us outperform the S\\&P 500 by more than 5,000% over the past 25 years.
 







 The
 **Senior Cybersecurity Engineer** 
 is responsible for helping protect Danaher's assets and data through cybersecurity, deploying new security tools and improve already existing tools. This role is part of a high performing team delivering essential cybersecurity services to our operating companies.
 







 This position is part of Danaher Information Security and will be remote.
 







**In this role, you will have the opportunity to:** 



* Design, implement, and maintain robust security solutionswithin the Microsoft cloud ecosystem, utilizing cutting\\-edge tools and technologies to ensure a secure, scalable, and resilient environment for the organization and its OpCos.
* Proactively identify and address security vulnerabilitiesand process gaps, working with cross\\-functional teams to enhance visibility, and deploy innovative security features that continuously strengthen the organization's defense mechanisms.
* Develop, implement, and enforce security policies, standards, and proceduresacross the organization to guarantee the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of sensitive data, while ensuring compliance with industry regulations and best practices.
* Collaborate with IT and operational teamsto integrate security considerations at every stage of the project, from design to testing, ensuring secure practices and reducing vulnerabilities in production systems.
* Drive the continuous improvement of security operationsby overseeing and refining standard work documentation, including processes for incident response, vulnerability management, and audit preparedness. This will ensure alignment with evolving security requirements and industry trends.







**The essential requirements of the job include:** 



* A minimum of 10 years of experiencein information technology (cybersecurity), with at least 7 years dedicated to system administration and security engineering, demonstrating a strong expertise in securing complex IT environments.
* An advanced understanding of Microsoft security and securing Microsoft solutions is required, including expertise in Active Directory and Entra ID, Microsoft's RAMP Architecture, and practical experience in areas such as Multi\\-Factor Authentication (MFA) and Single Sign\\-On (SSO). Proficiency in managing secure access through Conditional Access Policies is also essential, along with experience using Identity Protection for risk\\-based conditional access. Furthermore, the role requires familiarity with Azure AD Privileged Identity Management (PIM) for role management and access control, as well as experience with Intune, Microsoft Defender for Endpoint (MDE), and Mobile Application Management (MAM), and/or Microsoft Security Center.
* A foundational understanding of Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR) solutions is crucial, encompassing architecture and system management. This includes a solid grasp of core EDR principles and threat detection techniques, alongside operational expertise in managing and optimizing EDR systems for proactive threat monitoring and response.
* Python and PowerShell scripting proficiencyto automate security tasks, including integration with Windows endpoints, theCrowdStrike Falconplatform, and other security tools, streamlining operations and incident response workflows.
* Experience building custom integrationsbetween security tools and platforms, ensuring a cohesive, automated security infrastructure that supports threat detection, response, and remediation.







**It would be a plus if you also possess previous experience in and have or hold:** 



* Bachelor's degree in a related fieldor equivalent professional experience, demonstrating a strong foundation in technology or cybersecurity.
* An in\\-depth knowledge of Microsoft Intune is essential, including core Intune principles and its role in modern endpoint management. Operational expertise with Mobile Device Management (MDM), Mobile Application Management (MAM), and Microsoft Defender for Endpoint (MDE) is also required, ensuring effective protection across all managed devices.
* An advanced knowledge of CrowdStrike technologies is required, specifically including CrowdStrike Flight Control and CrowdStrike Query Language (FQL) for effective endpoint threat hunting and analysis. Expertise in utilizing the PSFalcon PowerShell module to interact with the CrowdStrike Falcon API is also essential for streamlined integration and automation of security operations.







 At Danaher we believe in designing a better, more sustainable workforce. We recognize the benefits of flexible, remote working arrangements for eligible roles and are committed to providing enriching careers, no matter the work arrangement. This position is eligible for a remote work arrangement in which you can work remotely from your home. Additional information about this remote work arrangement will be provided by your interview team. Explore the flexibility and challenge that working for Danaher can provide.
 







 The salary range for this role is $120,000 to $145,000\\. This is the range that we in good faith believe is the range of possible compensation for this role at the time of this posting. We may ultimately pay more or less than the posted range. This range may be modified in the future.
 







 This job is also eligible for bonus/incentive pay.
 







 We offer comprehensive package of benefits including paid time off, medical/dental/vision insurance and 401(k) to eligible employees.
 







 Note: No amount of pay is considered to be wages or compensation until such amount is earned, vested, and determinable. The amount and availability of any bonus, commission, benefits, or any other form of compensation and benefits that are allocable to a particular employee remains in the Company's sole discretion unless and until paid and may be modified at the Company's sole discretion, consistent with the law.

 Join our winning team today. Together, we'll accelerate the real\\-life impact of tomorrow's science and technology. We partner with customers across the globe to help them solve their most complex challenges, architecting solutions that bring the power of science to life.
 







 For more information, visit www.danaher.com.

title: OAG - Child Support | Technical Systems Analyst (Systems Analyst VI) | 25-0332
description:
GENERAL DESCRIPTION
   

 The Office of the Attorney General is a dynamic organization with over 4,000 employees throughout the State of Texas.  Our agency provides exemplary legal representation for every arm of the State, fights human trafficking, helps victims of crime, protects our constituents, and runs the most effective Child Support Enforcement program. 
   

 The Office of the Attorney General (OAG) of Texas is seeking a highly skilled and motivated Technical Systems Analyst to join our Applications Development Team. As a Technical Systems Analyst, you'll perform advanced computer systems analysis, development, and support for backend systems interfaces. This position focuses on managing and maintaining backend application architectures, ensuring smooth systems integration, and leading development efforts to align with Office of the Attorney General CSD’s organizational objectives.
   

 The role requires expertise in technical systems administration, backend system interface development, and high\\-level analysis. The ideal candidate demonstrates strong communication skills, effective collaboration in cross\\-functional teams, and the ability to manage complex technical projects. This position offers an opportunity to make meaningful contributions to Office of the Attorney General CSD’s mission through technical innovation and system excellence.
   

 The OAG is committed to providing innovative, modern, and value\\-driven IT services to the agency. We believe that having talented people in the right place while effectively utilizing new tools and technologies enables us to empower the agency to best serve the people of Texas. OAG employees enjoy excellent benefits (https://ers.texas.gov/Benefits\\-at\\-a\\-Glance) along with tremendous opportunities to do important work at a large, dynamic state agency making a positive difference in the lives of Texans.
   

 ESSENTIAL POSITION FUNCTIONS
   

 Backend Development and Support
   

 •    Design, develop, test, and support highly complex backend systems and interfaces to ensure seamless integration and reliable functionality.
   

 •    Perform rigorous testing, including integration testing, in collaboration with technical support teams to ensure product quality before release.
   

 •    Troubleshoot and resolve production issues to maintain operational uptime for customer\\-facing applications.
   

 •    Train IT staff on backend systems, tools, and processes to ensure consistent implementation and operational excellence.
   

 System Analysis and Development:
   

 •    Analyze business processes and system requirements to design and develop backend solutions that meet organizational needs.
   

 •    Create detailed technical specifications, data flow diagrams, and entity relationship diagrams for backend systems.
   

 •    Document all system development activities per Office of the Attorney General CSD’s Software Development Lifecycle and Project Management guidelines.
   

 •    Coordinate with supervisory staff to schedule and assign tasks effectively.
   

 System Evaluation and Integration:
   

 •    Evaluate and recommend improvements to existing backend systems and applications to enhance efficiency, scalability, and reliability.
   

 •    Ensure integration and compatibility of backend systems across various state agencies and organizational units.
   

 •    Develop and maintain secure, scalable interfaces for seamless data exchange between systems
   

 Process Improvement and Stakeholder Collaboration:
   

 •    Assess current business processes to identify and recommend areas for improvement.
   

 •    Collaborate with stakeholders to align backend system designs with organizational goals and regulatory requirements.
   

 •    Participate in disaster recovery, continuity of operations (COOP), and emergency response efforts as required.
   

 •    Fulfill other responsibilities assigned to support the agency’s operational needs.
   

 May lead, mentor and train others
   

 Performs related work as assigned
   

 Maintains relevant knowledge necessary to perform essential job functions
   

 Attends work regularly in compliance with agreed\\-upon work schedule. Telework schedules are permitted for employees based on the agency’s approved Telework Plan (if schedule does not adversely affect operations and service levels, and standard hours of operation are maintained). This role may require work outside regular hours and occasional travel to other work locations.
   

 Ensures security and confidentiality of sensitive and/or protected information
   

 Complies with all agency policies and procedures, including those pertaining to ethics and integrity
   

  

  





 MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS
   

 Education: Graduation from high school or equivalent
   

 Experience: Seven years of full\\-time experience working in the following (or closely related) fields: systems analysis, computer science, computer informationsystems, or management information systems; may substitute credit hours from an accredited college or university for the required experience on a year\\-for\\-year basis.
   

 Experience in high\\-level systems analysis, backend system interface development, and technical systems administration.
   

 Experience successfully managing stakeholder expectations and delivering solutions that align with business objectives and strategic goals.
   

 Knowledge of backend system interface management, including API design and implementation and GoAnywhere Interface Manager.
   

 Knowledge of advanced database technologies, including Postgres SQL, and associated management tools.
   

 Knowledge of high\\-level system design methodologies (e.g., entity\\-relationship modeling, data/process flow diagrams), object\\-oriented programming, and modern development frameworks.
   

 Knowledge of industry\\-standard integration tools, middleware technologies, secure coding practices, and system hardening.
   

 Knowledge and understanding of project management methodologies and techniques, including Agile.
   

 Skills in developing, maintaining, and optimizing backend systems and interfaces.
   

 Skills in interface file management, SQL development, triggers, and database optimization.
   

 Skills in implementing and troubleshooting API integrations and data exchange mechanisms.
   

 Skills in communicating effectively with technical, non\\-technical, and executive audiences.
   

 Skills in estimating and managing project timelines, resources, and risks.
   

 Ability to analyze and resolve complex backend system issues efficiently.
   

 Ability to plan, manage, and prioritize multiple projects under tight deadlines, with a focus on delivering high\\-quality results that meet or exceed stakeholder expectations.
   

 Ability to work both independently and collaboratively within cross\\-functional teams.
   

 Ability to interpret existing code and recommend improvements or modernization strategies.
   

 Ability to enforce coding standards and best practices across development teams.
   

 Ability to develop and present business cases for new or modified IT systems.
   

 Ability and commitment to upholding ethical standards and confidentiality in handling sensitive data and information.
   

 Ability to receive and respond positively to constructive feedback.
   

 Ability to work cooperatively with others in a professional environment, to include professional demeanor and integrity in all interactions and activities related to data analytics projects and responsibilities.
   

 Ability to work in person at an OAG work location, if needed.
   

 Ability to arrange for personal transportation for business\\-related travel, if needed.
   

 Ability to work more than 40 hours as needed and in compliance with the FLSA.
   

 Ability to lift and relocate 10 lbs.
   

 Ability to travel  up to 5%
   

 PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS
   

 Experience in managing and developing backend systems in a state or government agency environment.
   

 Proficiency in batch development tools like Talend.
   

 Proficiency in batch scheduling tools like Airflow.
   

 Experience with cloud platforms such as AWS or Azure for backend systems deployment.
   

 Certifications in relevant areas.
 



 TO APPLY
 



 To apply for a job with the OAG, electronic applications can be submitted through CAPPS Recruit. A State of Texas application must be completed to be considered, and paper applications are not accepted. Your application for this position may subject you to a criminal background check pursuant to the Texas Government Code. Military Crosswalk information can be accessed at http://www.hr.sao.state.tx.us/Compensation/MilitaryCrosswalk/MOSC\\_InformationTechnology.pdf. 
 



 THE OAG IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER

title: Project Manager-Siemens Real Estate (Midwest, East Coast, or Texas)
description:
Siemens Real Estate (SRE) wants you as our next Project Manager (Mid\\-West US Region). Are you wondering how we will work in the future. And how do we manage to put people at the center of this.
 



 How can buildings become the key to sustainable growth. And how can you save CO2 by collecting data. Then come to us, we look forward to receiving your application.
 



 Siemens Real Estate is responsible for Siemens' global real estate portfolio. Worldwide, we are responsible for 8\\.7 million square meters of office and production space at around 1,400 locations. We plan, build and design
 



 We operate and provide associated services. We are passionate about people, our planet and business requirements. We bring decades of experience and state\\-of\\-the\\-art technical know\\-how over the entire life cycle of real estate.
 



 We offer solutions for the transformation of our working world and for sustainable growth. You will need to be located in Midwest, East Coast, or Texas. As a Project Manager, your responsibilities would include, but not be limited to: Project Planning and Execution Develop comprehensive project plans, including schedules, cost estimates, and resource allocation.
 



 Coordinate with internal teams and external stakeholders to ensure project milestones are met. Monitor project progress and adjust as necessary to ensure successful completion. Plan and manage technical projects, ensuring they align with overall business objectives.
 



 Coordinate Siemens office requirements for furniture, space planning, IT, security, and other cross functional partners. Engagement of and coordination with Siemens EH\\&S, Security, IT, and AV project managers. Coordination, ordering, and installation oversight of furniture and equipment for projects.
 



 Stakeholder Management Serve as the primary point of contact for clients, contractors, and other stakeholders. Facilitate regular meetings to update stakeholders on project status and address any concerns. Ensure clear and consistent communication throughout the project lifecycle.
 



 Risk Management Identify potential project risks and develop mitigation strategies. Conduct regular risk assessments and implement contingency plans as needed. Ensure compliance with all relevant regulations and standards.
 



 Execute local Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) aspects to minimize risks and ensure legally compliant operations, fostering a zero\\-harm culture. Financial Oversight Manage project budgets, ensuring costs are controlled and financial objectives are met. Prepare and present financial reports to senior management.
 



 Approve expenditures and ensure all financial documentation is accurate and up to date. Develop detailed cost estimates for various types of projects, including expansions, fit\\-outs, lease end dates, maintenance, and new locations. Develop and implement technical concepts/projects to reduce costs.
 



 Quality Assurance Ensure all project deliverables meet the highest quality standards. Conduct regular site inspections and quality checks. Address any quality issues promptly and effectively.
 



 Team Leadership Lead and motivate project teams, providing guidance and support as needed. Foster a collaborative and productive team environment. Conduct performance reviews and provide feedback to team members.
 



 Compliance Ensure adherence to construction principles, guidelines, and processes. Steer and ensure adherence to local building standards and regulations, including proper documentation and required permits. Portfolio Management Manage a portfolio of 15\\-20 projects, ensuring each project is delivered on time and within budget.
 



 Project Communications Develop and implement communication plans to ensure all stakeholders are informed of project progress and changes. Prepare and distribute regular project updates, reports, and presentations. Facilitate effective communication between project teams, clients, and other stakeholders.
 



 Address any communication issues promptly to maintain project alignment and stakeholder satisfaction. Basic Requirements: Bachelor's degree in real estate, Construction Management, Business Administration, or a related field. 7\\+ years of experience in real estate, with a minimum of 5 years in project management within commercial real estate or construction sector.
 



 7\\+ years of experience of successfully managing mid to large\\-scale projects. Proficiency in project management software (e.g., MS Project) with a minimum of 5 years of experience using it to develop project schedules and show the critical path. 7\\+ years of experience in commercial/light warehouse construction to include mechanical, electrical, plumbing, building automation systems, and tenant improvement projects
 



 Ability to read and understand construction drawings and specifications. 10\\+ years of experience in strong project management skills, including the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously. 10\\+ years of experience using SharePoint.
 



 5\\+ years of experience with Microsoft Teams for collaborating across multiple groups. Ability and willingness to travel as needed for project site visits and stakeholder meetings. Must be authorized to work in the US without the need for sponsorship now or in the future.
 



 Preferred Requirements: Excellent communication and interpersonal skills. Solid understanding of financial management and budgeting. Strong problem\\-solving and decision\\-making abilities.
 



 Strong organizational skills and attention to detail. Ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines. Certifications PMP (Project Management Professional) certification preferred.
 



 LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) accreditation is a plus. You'll benefit from: Siemens offers a variety of health and wellness benefits to our employees. Details regarding our benefits can be found here: https://www.benefitsquickstart.com/siemens/index.html The pay range for this position is $89,670 to $153,720 and the annual target incentive will be 10% of the base salary
 



 The actual wage offered may be lower or higher depending on budget and candidate experience, knowledge, skills, qualifications, and premium geographic location. Transform the every day with us. About Siemens: We are a global technology company focused on industry, infrastructure, transport, and healthcare.
 



 From more resource\\-efficient factories, resilient supply chains, and smarter buildings and grids, to sustainable transportation as well as advanced healthcare, we create technology with the purpose of adding real value for customers. Our Commitment to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion: We value your unique identity and perspective. We are fully committed to providing equitable opportunities and building a workplace that reflects the diversity of society.
 



 Come bring your authentic self and create a better tomorrow with us. Learn more about our commitment to DEI here. Protecting the environment, conserving our natural resources, fostering the health and performance of our people as well as safeguarding their working conditions are core to our social and business commitment at Siemens.
 



 They are an integral part of our Business Conduct Guidelines and our corporate strategy. \\#LI\\-JE1 Equal Employment Opportunity Statement Siemens is an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer encouraging diversity in the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their race, color, creed, religion, national origin, citizenship status, ancestry, sex, age, physical or mental disability unrelated to ability, marital status, family responsibilities, pregnancy, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender expression, gender identity, transgender, sex stereotyping, order of protection status, protected veteran or military status, or an unfavorable discharge from military service, and other categories protected by federal, state or local law.
 



 Reasonable Accommodations If you require a reasonable accommodation in completing a job application, interviewing, completing any pre\\-employment testing, or otherwise participating in the employee selection process, please fill out the accommodations form by clicking on this link Accommodation for disability form. If you're unable to complete the form, you can reach out to our AskHR team for support at 1\\-866\\-743\\-6367\\. Please note our AskHR representatives do not have visibility of application or interview status.

title: Enterprise Architect 3-529501308
description:
LEVEL DESCRIPTION:
 
 · 8 or more years of experience, relies on experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals, independently performs a variety of complicated tasks, may lead and direct the work of others, a wide degree of creativity and latitude is expected.
 



 JOB DESCRIPTION:
 



 Responsible for translating the client's business requirements into specific systems, applications or process designs with interlocked financial modeling for very large complex technical solutions. Analyzes customer service requirements and designs service solutions to meet those objectives. Primary expert to construct the specific solution, scope document, risk profile, and corresponding financials. Maintains and utilizes detailed industry and internal services knowledge in the construction of industry\\-leading services solutions, including expert working level knowledge of the processes, technologies, and people components involved in the services arena. Uses expertise to construct specific and detailed solutions that encompass process, technology, and staffing plans for customer sales opportunities. Constructs risk assessments and corresponding remediation plans relative to complex services proposals. Participates in the construction of detailed financial models that align with complex services proposals. Composes Statement of Work or other documents, using departmental automation tools as available, to craft detailed and accurate deliverables that specify processes, technology, staffing, and project management involved in proposed services solutions. As needed, provide a "trusted expert advisor" role as a Subject Matter Expert for technical services, to both internal and external customers, ranging from formal advice to internal and external customer presentations. Follow all organizational Standard Operating Procedures relative to cost modeling, approvals and reviews, and all other associated workflow and deliverables.
 



 ADDITIONAL JOB DETAILS AND SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS
 



 The Salesforce Architect acts as a "trusted expert advisor" and Subject Matter Expert for technical services. They assess current systems, identify weaknesses, and review business processes. They provide design recommendations, conduct risk assessments, and suggest performance and security optimizations to align Salesforce implementation with best practices and business goals.
 



 This role stabilizes Salesforce Orgs and addresses potential vulnerabilities. Responsibilities include making technical decisions, supporting team members, and ensuring task completion. The individual communicates effectively, offers best practice advice, and guides system configurations. They participate in daily sprints and stand\\-up meetings, monitor developer code changes, and determine solutions with timelines. They collaborate with designers, developers, network architects, security analysts, and program teams to maintain architectural standards. They prepare project models or diagrams and facilitate communication between customers and technical teams. Experience with Agile methodologies is required, and they must be available for on\\-call support, providing development and hands\\-on configuration as needed.
 



 CANDIDATE SKILLS AND QUALIFICATIONS:
 



 Minimum Requirements: Candidates that do not meet or exceed the minimum stated requirements (skills/experience) will be displayed to customers but may not be chosen for this opportunity.
 



 Years Required/Preferred Experience
 



 8 Required Design and deliver healthy Salesforce implementations for enterprise\\-grade customers using Salesforce products.
 



 8 Required Designed organization strategy and data model for multiple Salesforce implementations
 



 8 Required Designed technical solutions for identity and access, implemented data and process integrations, and designed solutions that account for large data volumes and data privacy needs.
 



 8 Required Experience in all End\\-to\\-End technical aspects of a Salesforce.com program: data migrations, data quality, systems integrations, 3rd party applications, AppExchange products, and custom development.
 



 8 Required Experience in Salesforce implementation and development and in writing Apex programming
 



 8 Required Visual force pages, Apex triggers, Aura Components, and lightning web components. Knowledge in implementing solutions using configurations (no\\-code) such as Flows, pr
 



 8 Required Experience with release management, source control, and deployment technologies such as CI/CD pipelines, Metadata API, and integration services
 



 8 Required Experience with cross\\-cloud Salesforce (SFDC) implementations integrated with other cloud and on\\-premises systems
 



 8 Required A solid understanding of the architectural principles of cloud\\-based platforms, including SaaS, PaaS, multitenancy, multitiered infrastructure, integration patterns, and application servers
 



 8 Required Well versed with human centric user experience and software design principles
 



 8 Required Well versed with Salesforce well architected framework

title: Head of Insurance
description:
Steadily is an insurance technology company that specializes in rental property insurance for landlords. We’re four years old, 160 people, manage $20B in risk, and are intent on becoming the world’s best and largest insurer of rental properties.
 



 We exist to deliver fast, affordable insurance and to pay claims quickly and fairly. To do that, we hire the best engineers, actuaries, sales, and service people in the country to build the experience that we’d want if we were the client.
 



 Steadily is hiring the
 **Head of Insurance** 
 to lead our exceptional insurance org. You will have the ultimate responsibility for pricing sophistication, market penetration, product innovation, and underwriting profitability. If you enjoy leading high performers and being extremely hands\\-on, this is the role for you. 
 



 The scope of responsibilities may include actuarial, reinsurance, product, underwriting, and claims. This role is flexible in terms of title and responsibilities so if you have experience in some areas but not all, let’s talk.
 







**What You'll Do** 



* Have ultimate responsibility for growth, sophistication, and profitability of our products.
* Collaborate closely with external partners including carriers, reinsurers, vendors, brokers, agents, etc. Lay the tracks for us to continue scaling quickly by leveraging your relationships in the reinsurance and carrier market.
* Develop ongoing actuarial processes to ensure ongoing market, program, and state level profitability.
* Construct models, workflows, and various other means of automation to reduce overhead and expenses in your org.
* Drive innovation by finding new methods to price risk better than the traditional solutions. Develop cutting edge, data\\-driven enhancements to our risk model.
* Continue leading the expansion of our internal claims operation. Use technology solutions to reduce cycle times, improve the customer experience and manage loss costs.
* Work with the actuarial team to build out a reserve methodology.
* You will roll up your sleeves and work alongside your high performing teams to get the job done. No task is beneath you.







**Your Background** 



* **Experienced** 
 : You have a stellar track record of growth and profitability. You’re an accomplished insurance leader with a minimum of 10 years of experience in P\\&C at a carrier or MGA. You have deep knowledge of reinsurance structures, pricing, and contracts. Your track record speaks for itself and gives you instant credibility.
* **Network** 
 : You have a lengthy rolodex of industry contacts you can leverage.
* **Education:** 
 CPCU and/or actuarial credentials are a plus.
* **Leadership:** 
 You know how to build and lead a high performing team. Your team members respect you for both how competent you are and how you never ask them to do anything you wouldn’t do yourself.
* **Builder** 
 : You have a builder’s mindset and can take projects and products from inception to launch and beyond. You have a bias towards action.
* **Digital** 
 : Your tech savvy is exceptional. You have strong product sense and are a master of learning and implementing new software and processes. Your technical and analytical skills are top notch.
* **Hungry** 
 : You want to make the leap into pre\\-IPO tech company to do things you’ve never done before. You want to roll up your sleeves and hustle – you are not looking for a traditional 9\\-5 job.







**Compensation and Benefits** 



* We ensure our compensation is 90th percentile for every role. This role will include meaningful equity in the company.
* PTO and six federal holidays
* Health insurance including Medical, Dental, Vision, Life, HSA, FSA
* 401K
* In office 4 days a week, Wednesday is a company\\-wide no\\-meeting day
* Free snacks \\& regular team lunches







**Locations** 



* Overland Park, KS or Austin, TX
* Generous relocation package available for out of state candidates







**Why Join Us** 



* You'll be in good company. Our founders have three successful startups under their belt and have recruited a stellar team to match.
* We pay top of market (see comp).
* We're earlier stage, so you'll get to wear a lot of hats and shape product decisions.
* We have a good time. Culture matters a ton to us.
* We're growing fast and are exceptionally well\\-funded.
* Steadily boasts a very unique culture that our teammates love. We call it like we see it and we’re nothing if not candid. Check out our culture deck here to learn what we’re all about.
* Steadily was awarded Comparably’s Best Company Leadership 2023, Best CEOs for Women 2023, and Best Company for Women 2022







**We’re excited to meet you!**

title: Cryptographic Key Operations Lead, Vice President, Hybrid
description:
**Who we are looking for** 




 State Street is seeking an experienced Cryptographic Key Operations Lead to oversee the end\\-to\\-end lifecycle management of cryptographic keys across cloud, on\\-premises, infrastructure and IoT environments. This role ensures the secure generation, distribution, rotation, revocation, and retirement of encryption keys while maintaining compliance with regulatory and security policies. Additionally, the Key Operations Lead will manage and mentor a team of Key Management Engineers, driving operational excellence and automation to enhance key lifecycle processes. This role requires close collaboration with security, IT, cloud, infrastructure, and application teams to maintain the availability, reliability, and security of key management services, supporting business\\-critical operations and financial transactions.
 







 This role can be performed in a hybrid model, where you can balance work from home and office to match your needs and role requirements.
 







**What you will be responsible for** 



* Lead and manage a team of Key Management Engineers, providing guidance, mentoring, and technical leadership to ensure effective cryptographic key lifecycle management.
* Oversee the daily operations and security of cryptographic key management, ensuring compliance with financial industry regulations e.g. (PCI DSS, GDPR, FIPS 140\\-2/3\\).
* Drive the secure generation, storage, distribution, rotation, revocation, and retirement of encryption keys across cloud, on\\-premises, and IoT environments.
* Monitor and respond to key management incidents, such as key compromise, expiration, or policy violations, ensuring timely remediation and risk mitigation.
* Collaborate with security, cloud, infrastructure, and DevSecOps teams to integrate cryptographic services into enterprise applications, infrastructure and IoT security frameworks.
* Optimize and automate key management processes, leveraging APIs, key management platforms (KMS), security orchestration tools, and infrastructure\\-as\\-code (IaC) methodologies.
* Ensure high availability and reliability of key management services to support secure transactions and data protection.







**What we value** 




 These skills will help you succeed in this role
 


* Develop and maintain detailed documentation of key management processes, procedures, and operational workflows.
* Provide reporting and analysis on key usage, compliance, performance metrics, and risk exposure to senior leadership and auditors.
* Stay up to date with emerging cryptographic technologies, security threats, and regulatory changes, ensuring that key management practices evolve accordingly.







**Education \\& Preferred Qualifications** 



* Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Cybersecurity, Information Security, or related field or equivalent work experience.
* 8\\+ years of experience in key management operations, cryptographic security, or information security within a financial institution or other regulated environment.
* Strong expertise in cryptographic key lifecycle management, including symmetric and asymmetric encryption, PKI, and HSMs (Hardware Security Modules).
* Experience with enterprise key management solutions (AWS KMS, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault, OCI KMS)
* Familiarity with financial security regulations and standards, such as PCI DSS, FIPS 140\\-2/3, and NIST guidelines.
* Security certifications such as CISM, CISSP, CCSP, and AWS Security Specialty.
* Experience with post\\-quantum cryptography (PQC) readiness and emerging cryptographic frameworks.
* Experience with JIRA and Confluence.







**Additional requirements** 




 Travel up to 25% may be required
 







**Are you the right candidate? Yes!** 




 We truly believe in the power that comes from the diverse backgrounds and experiences our employees bring with them. Although each vacancy details what we are looking for, we don't necessarily need you to fulfil all of them when applying. If you like change and innovation, seek to see the bigger picture, make data driven decisions and are a good team player, you could be a great fit.
 







**Why this role is important to us** 




 Our technology function, Global Technology Services (GTS), is vital to State Street and is the key enabler for our business to deliver data and insights to our clients. We're driving the company's digital transformation and expanding business capabilities using industry best practices and advanced technologies such as cloud, artificial intelligence and robotics process automation.
 







 We offer a collaborative environment where technology skills and innovation are valued in a global organization. We're looking for top technical talent to join our team and deliver creative technology solutions that help us become an end\\-to\\-end, next\\-generation financial services company.
 







 Join us if you want to grow your technical skills, solve real problems and make your mark on our industry.
 







**About State Street** 




**What we do.** 
 State Street is one of the largest custodian banks, asset managers and asset intelligence companies in the world. From technology to product innovation, we're making our mark on the financial services industry. For more than two centuries, we've been helping our clients safeguard and steward the investments of millions of people. We provide investment servicing, data \\& analytics, investment research \\& trading and investment management to institutional clients.
 







**Work, Live and Grow.** 
 We make all efforts to create a great work environment. Our benefits packages are competitive and comprehensive. Details vary by location, but you may expect generous medical care, insurance and savings plans, among other perks. You'll have access to flexible Work Programs to help you match your needs. And our wealth of development programs and educational support will help you reach your full potential.
 







**Inclusion, Diversity and Social Responsibility.** 
 We truly believe our employees' diverse backgrounds, experiences and perspectives are a powerful contributor to creating an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive and reach their maximum potential while adding value to both our organization and our clients. We warmly welcome candidates of diverse origin, background, ability, age, sexual orientation, gender identity and personality. Another fundamental value at State Street is active engagement with our communities around the world, both as a partner and a leader. You will have tools to help balance your professional and personal life, paid volunteer days, matching gift programs and access to employee networks that help you stay connected to what matters to you.
 



 State Street is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer.
 







**Salary Range:** 



 $130,000 \\- $205,000 Annual
 




 The range quoted above applies to the role in the primary location specified. If the candidate would ultimately work outside of the primary location above, the applicable range could differ.
 







**Job Application Disclosure:** 




 It is unlawful in Massachusetts to require or administer a lie detector test as a condition of employment or continued employment. An employer who violates this law shall be subject to criminal penalties and civil liability.
 







 State Street's Speak Up Line
