title: Fill-in Optometrist (March 2025- August 2025)
description:
**About SharpeVision:** 
  





 Be part of the change. Join SharpeVision and work with a national leader in refractive surgery bringing clear, unencumbered sight to people from around the world. We are modern, transformative vision\\-correction boutiques located in Seattle, Chicago and Austin. Our goal is to help our patients realize their full human potential. We believe in people and the magic that happens when they focus on a common goal. We believe in the power of technology to transform lives, and we believe we are here to be part of it. The day is coming when no adult will need to put plastic in their eyes or on their face to see clearly. At SharpeVision, we are bringing that day closer, one patient at a time.
 



**Summary:** 




 SVML Optometrists combine exceptional work ethic, high energy and an outstanding personality, with a deep technical understanding of optometry. Our optometrists are highly organized, thorough and detail\\-oriented, with the ability to effectively adapt to a fast\\-paced team environment. They are committed to providing a comfortable and successful service and experience for all of our patients. They are reliable, responsible, dependable, honest and ethical. They are socially perceptive to patients’ needs and feelings. They have an understanding of their impact on Company outcomes and results and are dedicated to producing superior work.
 



**Essential Duties and Responsibilities** 
 include the following. Other duties may be assigned.
 



 \\* Develops positive optometrist\\-patient relationships.
 



 \\* Evaluates patients for LASIK or other refractive surgery and makes recommendations as to treatment options to the Ophthalmologist.
 



 \\* Works together with the Ophthalmologist to achieve the best possible outcome for all patients.
 



 \\* Demonstrates mastery of pre\\- and post\\-operative care for patients.
 



 \\* Executes consistent and specific medical protocol.
 



 \\* Trains patients or caregivers in techniques for managing at\\-home care.
 



 \\* Provides leadership, management, and accountability for timely patient appointments.
 



 \\* Represents the organization within the public, medical, and business community.
 



 \\* Records and maintains clinical and business data in written and/or electronic form.
 



 \\* Participation in co\\-management and related special projects.
 



**In addition to a modern, progressive, and friendly team culture, we offer:** 




 · Competitive Pay\\- Daily Per Diem Rate
 



**Qualifications:** 




 To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform essential functions.
 



**Education/Experience:** 




 Doctor of Optometry (OD) degree from an accredited School of Optometry.
 



**Language Ability:** 




 Fluency of the English language. Excellent oral and written comprehension and expression. Speech clarity and recognition. Active listening. Ability to read, analyze, and interpret related medical, scientific, and technical journals. Ability to respond to common inquiries and provide information to patients, vendors, colleagues, and business community members. Good interpersonal and presentation skills.
 



**Math Ability:** 




 Ability to use mathematical methods or formulas for related medical and scientific measurements and calculations. Ability to calculate percentages. Ability to compile, tabulate, or verify information or data.
 



**Reasoning Ability:** 




 Ability to collect data, establish facts, and draw valid conclusions. Ability to interpret technical instructions in mathematical or diagram form. Ability to use logic. Ability to identify information by categorizing, recognizing differences or similarities, and detecting changes.
 



**Computer Skills:** 
 Microsoft Office Suite, Email, Calendar and Scheduling Software, Medical Software, Internet, Data Entry
 



**Certificates and Licenses:** 




 Licensed to practice Optometry in Texas State prior to beginning. Excellent standing with all licensure authorities.
 



**Supervisory Responsibilities:** 




 This position may supervise and/or assist employees relative to specific tasks or projects but has no direct reports.

 The work environment characteristics described here represent those an employee encounters while performing this job's essential functions. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform essential functions. The noise level in the work environment is usually low to moderate. The work environment is indoors and environmentally controlled. The work environment is structured. May have exposure to disease or infections.

description:
**Job Description: Enterprise Architect 3 (Salesforce Architect)** 




**Primary Work Location:** 
 701 W 49th Street, Austin, TX 78751\\.
 



**Hybrid Position:** 
 Onsite on Mondays, remote Tuesday through Friday (tentative, subject to change).
 







**Note: Need someone with State/Federal client experience and must be local to Austin, TX.** 








**Position Overview** 




 The Enterprise Architect 3 is responsible for translating business requirements into technical solutions, providing expert guidance in designing complex systems, applications, and process solutions. The individual will lead in creating scope documents, risk profiles, and financial models while ensuring adherence to architectural standards. The Salesforce Architect role involves assessing systems, identifying weaknesses, designing solutions, and providing hands\\-on configuration and development as needed.
 







**Key Responsibilities** 



* Design and deliver Salesforce implementations for large enterprise customers using Salesforce products.
* Develop organization strategy and data models for multiple Salesforce implementations.
* Design technical solutions for identity, access management, data/process integrations, and ensure solutions address large data volumes and privacy needs.
* Oversee all aspects of Salesforce programs, including data migrations, integrations, third\\-party applications, AppExchange products, and custom development.
* Expertise in writing Apex programming, Visual Force pages, Aura components, Lightning web components, and implementing solutions using configurations (e.g., Flows).
* Manage release processes, source control, and deployment technologies like CI/CD pipelines, Metadata API, and integration services.
* Lead cross\\-cloud Salesforce implementations integrated with other cloud and on\\-premises systems.
* Apply architectural principles of cloud\\-based platforms, including SaaS, PaaS, integration patterns, and multitiered infrastructures.
* Ensure that systems align with user experience and software design principles.
* Adhere to Salesforce's well\\-architected framework to ensure best practices.
* Participate in daily sprints, assist team members, monitor code changes, and offer solutions to meet deadlines.
* Collaborate with designers, developers, network architects, security analysts, and other technical teams.
* Serve as a trusted advisor for technical services, offering presentations, advice, and guidance.







**Qualifications** 



* 8\\+ years of experience designing and delivering Salesforce implementations.
* Expertise in designing Salesforce organization strategy and data models.
* In\\-depth experience with identity/access management, data integrations, and large data volumes.
* Proficiency in Salesforce Apex programming, Visual Force pages, Aura components, and Lightning web components.
* Experience with cross\\-cloud Salesforce implementations and integrating systems.
* Strong understanding of cloud architectures, SaaS, PaaS, multitenancy, and integration patterns.
* Ability to provide hands\\-on development and configuration when needed.
* Knowledge of release management, source control, and deployment technologies (e.g., CI/CD, Metadata API).
* Expertise in Salesforce's well\\-architected framework and applying software design principles.







**Work Hours and Location** 



* **Normal Business Hours:** 
 Monday through Friday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM, excluding state holidays.
* **Local Candidates Only:** 
 Candidates must be located within Austin or surrounding areas.
* **Travel Expenses:** 
 Any travel, per diem, parking, or living expenses are the responsibility of the candidate/vendor unless pre\\-approved in writing by the agency.
* **Work Outside Normal Hours:** 
 The candidate may be required to work evenings, weekends, or holidays as requested. Payment for overtime (over 40 hours/week) must be pre\\-approved.







**Other Special Requirements** 



* Interviews will be conducted via Microsoft Teams.
* The position is hybrid, requiring in\\-office work on designated days and flexibility for remote work.

title: Sr. Engineer II, Cloud - Next-Gen SIEM (Remote)
description:
**About the Role:** 

 Are you passionate about building cutting\\-edge cloud\\-based security solutions? Do you thrive on solving complex problems in high\\-volume, data\\-intensive environments? CrowdStrike is seeking a Senior Engineer II \\- Cloud to join our elite CrowdStrike Falcon® Next\\-Gen SIEM team and drive the development of our advanced detections and user and entity behavior analytics (UEBA) solutions. In this role, you'll be at the forefront of designing and implementing innovative features that can handle trillions of events per day, empowering organizations to defend against sophisticated cyber threats with unprecedented efficiency. If you're ready to architect systems that operate at massive scale and make a significant impact on the future of cybersecurity, we want to hear from you.
 






**What We’re All About:** 

 At CrowdStrike, we stop breaches.
 







 We’re here to protect data, systems, technology – and, most importantly, the people they serve. Our cloud\\-based security is the first line of defense for the data we safeguard, and we are proud of that. Because we know how important our software is, we work fiercely to make sure that what we create works for everyone who needs it, every time. 
 







 We believe in one team, one fight, and our everyday work reflects that – our teams respect every member, and the people we work with care about the product and each other. We also understand that life is just as important as work, and treat time off and flexibility accordingly. We trust you to get the job done without having someone looking over your shoulder.
 






**What You’ll Do:** 
* Lead the design and development of cloud\\-native microservices for our Next\\-Gen SIEM platform, focusing on detections and UEBA capabilities that can process and analyze trillions of events per day.
* Take end\\-to\\-end ownership of complex, high\\-impact projects across multiple teams, driving technical decisions and providing architectural guidance using collaborative tools like Miro.
* Partner with cross\\-functional teams to define, design, and implement solutions that enhance threat detection and analysis capabilities. Contribute to the medium\\-term strategic and technical direction by identifying areas of greatest need, and creating plans for improvement.
* Utilize and integrate technologies such as Go, Kafka, Redis, OpenSearch, PostgreSQL, and more to build robust, scalable solutions.
* Optimize and scale existing systems for improved stability, performance, and reliability across business\\-critical infrastructure, using monitoring tools like Grafana to track and analyze system metrics.
* Mentor junior engineers through pair programming, code reviews, and knowledge sharing, fostering a culture of technical excellence. Additionally, participate in the interview process and coach/mentor new interviewers to maintain high hiring standards.
* Champion software engineering best practices to ensure high\\-quality deliverables, including robust testing strategies, effective code reviews, comprehensive documentation, continuous integration/deployment, and adherence to architectural principles that promote scalability and maintainability.
* Participate in and lead technical working groups that influence the broader Product team or industry.
* Provide monitoring and operational support for production services, including participating in an on\\-call rotation for one week approximately every 10\\-12 weeks.
* Be given the autonomy to own your work in a high trust environment, managing tasks and priorities effectively using Jira.






**What You’ll Need:** 
* Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent experience.
* 8\\+ years of experience in software development, with a focus on cloud\\-native architectures and distributed systems.
* Expert\\-level proficiency in at least one modern programming language such as Go (preferred), Python, Java, or C\\#.
* Demonstrated experience in designing and implementing large\\-scale, high\\-performance data processing systems.
* Strong understanding of security concepts, threat detection methodologies, and UEBA principles.
* Proven track record of leading complex technical projects and delivering results on schedule.
* Experience with cloud platforms (preferably AWS) and containerization technologies like Docker and Kubernetes.
* Excellent communication skills, with the ability to explain complex technical concepts to both technical and non\\-technical audiences.
* A collaborative mindset and the ability to work effectively across teams and disciplines.






**Bonus Points:** 
* Prior experience working in cybersecurity or intelligence fields.
* Experience in developing or working with SIEM or log management solutions.
* Experience with big data technologies such as Kafka, OpenSearch, Cassandra, Spark, or Flink.
* Familiarity with machine learning and AI techniques applied to cybersecurity.
